44// This simplified cast function doesn't need to worry about advanced concepts like
45// depth range values, or casting to bool.
46template <typename DestT, typename SrcT>
47DestT UniformStateQueryCast(SrcT value);
48
49// From-Float-To-Integer Casts
50template <>
51GLint UniformStateQueryCast(GLfloat value)
52{
53 return clampCast<GLint>(roundf(value));
54}
55
56template <>
57GLuint UniformStateQueryCast(GLfloat value)
58{
59 return clampCast<GLuint>(roundf(value));
60}
61
62// From-Integer-to-Integer Casts
63template <>
64GLint UniformStateQueryCast(GLuint value)
65{
66 return clampCast<GLint>(value);
67}
68
69template <>
70GLuint UniformStateQueryCast(GLint value)
71{
72 return clampCast<GLuint>(value);
73}
74
75// From-Boolean-to-Anything Casts
76template <>
77GLfloat UniformStateQueryCast(GLboolean value)
78{
79 return (ConvertToBool(value) ? 1.0f : 0.0f);
80}
81
82template <>
83GLint UniformStateQueryCast(GLboolean value)
84{
85 return (ConvertToBool(value) ? 1 : 0);
86}
87
88template <>
89GLuint UniformStateQueryCast(GLboolean value)
90{
91 return (ConvertToBool(value) ? 1u : 0u);
92}
93
94// Default to static_cast
95template <typename DestT, typename SrcT>
96DestT UniformStateQueryCast(SrcT value)
97{
98 return static_cast<DestT>(value);
99}
100
101template <typename SrcT, typename DestT>
102void UniformStateQueryCastLoop(DestT *dataOut, const uint8_t *srcPointer, int components)
103{
104 for (int comp = 0; comp < components; ++comp)
105 {
106 // We only work with strides of 4 bytes for uniform components. (GLfloat/GLint)
107 // Don't use SrcT stride directly since GLboolean has a stride of 1 byte.
108 size_t offset = comp * 4;
109 const SrcT *typedSrcPointer = reinterpret_cast<const SrcT *>(&srcPointer[offset]);
110 dataOut[comp] = UniformStateQueryCast<DestT>(*typedSrcPointer);
111 }
112}

114template <typename VarT>
115GLuint GetResourceIndexFromName(const std::vector<VarT> &list, const std::string &name)
116{
117 std::string nameAsArrayName = name + "[0]";
118 for (size_t index = 0; index < list.size(); index++)
119 {
120 const VarT &resource = list[index];
121 if (resource.name == name || (resource.isArray() && resource.name == nameAsArrayName))
122 {
123 return static_cast<GLuint>(index);
124 }
125 }
126
127 return GL_INVALID_INDEX;
128}
129
130GLint GetVariableLocation(const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &list,
131 const std::vector<VariableLocation> &locationList,
132 const std::string &name)
133{
134 size_t nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex;
135 unsigned int arrayIndex = ParseArrayIndex(name, &nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex);
136
137 for (size_t location = 0u; location < locationList.size(); ++location)
138 {
139 const VariableLocation &variableLocation = locationList[location];
140 if (!variableLocation.used())
141 {
142 continue;
143 }
144
145 const sh::ShaderVariable &variable = list[variableLocation.index];
146
147 // Array output variables may be bound out of order, so we need to ensure we only pick the
148 // first element if given the base name.
149 if ((variable.name == name) && (variableLocation.arrayIndex == 0))
150 {
151 return static_cast<GLint>(location);
152 }
153 if (variable.isArray() && variableLocation.arrayIndex == arrayIndex &&
154 angle::BeginsWith(variable.name, name, nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex))
155 {
156 return static_cast<GLint>(location);
157 }
158 }
159
160 return -1;
161}
162
163GLint GetVariableLocation(const std::vector<LinkedUniform> &list,
164 const std::vector<VariableLocation> &locationList,
165 const std::string &name)
166{
167 size_t nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex;
168 unsigned int arrayIndex = ParseArrayIndex(name, &nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex);
169
170 for (size_t location = 0u; location < locationList.size(); ++location)
171 {
172 const VariableLocation &variableLocation = locationList[location];
173 if (!variableLocation.used())
174 {
175 continue;
176 }
177
178 const LinkedUniform &variable = list[variableLocation.index];
179
180 // Array output variables may be bound out of order, so we need to ensure we only pick the
181 // first element if given the base name. Uniforms don't allow this behavior and some code
182 // seemingly depends on the opposite behavior, so only enable it for output variables.
183 if (angle::BeginsWith(variable.name, name) && (variableLocation.arrayIndex == 0))
184 {
185 if (name.length() == variable.name.length())
186 {
187 ASSERT(name == variable.name);
188 // GLES 3.1 November 2016 page 87.
189 // The string exactly matches the name of the active variable.
190 return static_cast<GLint>(location);
191 }
192 if (name.length() + 3u == variable.name.length() && variable.isArray())
193 {
194 ASSERT(name + "[0]" == variable.name);
195 // The string identifies the base name of an active array, where the string would
196 // exactly match the name of the variable if the suffix "[0]" were appended to the
197 // string.
198 return static_cast<GLint>(location);
199 }
200 }
201 if (variable.isArray() && variableLocation.arrayIndex == arrayIndex &&
202 nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex + 3u == variable.name.length() &&
203 angle::BeginsWith(variable.name, name, nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex))
204 {
205 ASSERT(name.substr(0u, nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex) + "[0]" == variable.name);
206 // The string identifies an active element of the array, where the string ends with the
207 // concatenation of the "[" character, an integer (with no "+" sign, extra leading
208 // zeroes, or whitespace) identifying an array element, and the "]" character, the
209 // integer is less than the number of active elements of the array variable, and where
210 // the string would exactly match the enumerated name of the array if the decimal
211 // integer were replaced with zero.
212 return static_cast<GLint>(location);
213 }
214 }
215
216 return -1;
217}

219void CopyStringToBuffer(GLchar *buffer,
220 const std::string &string,
221 GLsizei bufSize,
222 GLsizei *lengthOut)
223{
224 ASSERT(bufSize > 0);
225 size_t length = std::min<size_t>(bufSize - 1, string.length());
226 memcpy(buffer, string.c_str(), length);
227 buffer[length] = '\0';
228
229 if (lengthOut)
230 {
231 *lengthOut = static_cast<GLsizei>(length);
232 }
233}

235bool IncludeSameArrayElement(const std::set<std::string> &nameSet, const std::string &name)
236{
237 std::vector<unsigned int> subscripts;
238 std::string baseName = ParseResourceName(name, &subscripts);
239 for (const std::string &nameInSet : nameSet)
240 {
241 std::vector<unsigned int> arrayIndices;
242 std::string arrayName = ParseResourceName(nameInSet, &arrayIndices);
243 if (baseName == arrayName &&
244 (subscripts.empty() || arrayIndices.empty() || subscripts == arrayIndices))
245 {
246 return true;
247 }
248 }
249 return false;
250}

252std::string GetInterfaceBlockLimitName(ShaderType shaderType, sh::BlockType blockType)
253{
254 std::ostringstream stream;
255 stream << "GL_MAX_" << GetShaderTypeString(shaderType) << "_";
256
257 switch (blockType)
258 {
259 case sh::BlockType::BLOCK_UNIFORM:
260 stream << "UNIFORM_BUFFERS";
261 break;
262 case sh::BlockType::BLOCK_BUFFER:
263 stream << "SHADER_STORAGE_BLOCKS";
264 break;
265 default:
266 UNREACHABLE();
267 return "";
268 }
269
270 if (shaderType == ShaderType::Geometry)
271 {
272 stream << "_EXT";
273 }
274
275 return stream.str();
276}

287 UNREACHABLE();
288 return "";
289 }

292void LogInterfaceBlocksExceedLimit(InfoLog &infoLog,
293 ShaderType shaderType,
294 sh::BlockType blockType,
295 GLuint limit)
296{
297 infoLog << GetShaderTypeString(shaderType) << " shader "

301
302bool ValidateInterfaceBlocksCount(GLuint maxInterfaceBlocks,
303 const std::vector<sh::InterfaceBlock> &interfaceBlocks,
304 ShaderType shaderType,
305 sh::BlockType blockType,
306 GLuint *combinedInterfaceBlocksCount,
307 InfoLog &infoLog)
308{
309 GLuint blockCount = 0;
310 for (const sh::InterfaceBlock &block : interfaceBlocks)
311 {
312 if (IsActiveInterfaceBlock(block))
313 {
314 blockCount += std::max(block.arraySize, 1u);
315 if (blockCount > maxInterfaceBlocks)
316 {
317 LogInterfaceBlocksExceedLimit(infoLog, shaderType, blockType, maxInterfaceBlocks);
318 return false;
319 }
320 }
321 }
322
323 // [OpenGL ES 3.1] Chapter 7.6.2 Page 105:
324 // If a uniform block is used by multiple shader stages, each such use counts separately
325 // against this combined limit.
326 // [OpenGL ES 3.1] Chapter 7.8 Page 111:
327 // If a shader storage block in a program is referenced by multiple shaders, each such
328 // reference counts separately against this combined limit.
329 if (combinedInterfaceBlocksCount)
330 {
331 *combinedInterfaceBlocksCount += blockCount;
332 }
333
334 return true;
335}
336
337GLuint GetInterfaceBlockIndex(const std::vector<InterfaceBlock> &list, const std::string &name)
338{
339 std::vector<unsigned int> subscripts;
340 std::string baseName = ParseResourceName(name, &subscripts);
341
342 unsigned int numBlocks = static_cast<unsigned int>(list.size());
343 for (unsigned int blockIndex = 0; blockIndex < numBlocks; blockIndex++)
344 {
345 const auto &block = list[blockIndex];
346 if (block.name == baseName)
347 {
348 const bool arrayElementZero =
349 (subscripts.empty() && (!block.isArray || block.arrayElement == 0));
350 const bool arrayElementMatches =
351 (subscripts.size() == 1 && subscripts[0] == block.arrayElement);
352 if (arrayElementMatches || arrayElementZero)
353 {
354 return blockIndex;
355 }
356 }
357 }
358
359 return GL_INVALID_INDEX;
360}

362void GetInterfaceBlockName(const GLuint index,
363 const std::vector<InterfaceBlock> &list,
364 GLsizei bufSize,
365 GLsizei *length,
366 GLchar *name)
367{
368 ASSERT(index < list.size());
369
370 const auto &block = list[index];
371
372 if (bufSize > 0)
373 {
374 std::string blockName = block.name;
375
376 if (block.isArray)
377 {
378 blockName += ArrayString(block.arrayElement);
379 }
380 CopyStringToBuffer(name, blockName, bufSize, length);
381 }
382}

408// Find the matching varying or field by name.
409const sh::ShaderVariable *FindOutputVaryingOrField(const ProgramMergedVaryings &varyings,
410 ShaderType stage,
411 const std::string &name)
412{
413 const sh::ShaderVariable *var = nullptr;
414 for (const ProgramVaryingRef &ref : varyings)
415 {
416 if (ref.frontShaderStage != stage)
417 {
418 continue;
419 }
420
421 const sh::ShaderVariable *varying = ref.get(stage);
422 if (varying->name == name)
423 {
424 var = varying;
425 break;
426 }
427 GLuint fieldIndex = 0;
428 var = varying->findField(name, &fieldIndex);
429 if (var != nullptr)
430 {
431 break;
432 }
433 }
434 return var;
435}

437void AddParentPrefix(const std::string &parentName, std::string *mismatchedFieldName)
438{
439 ASSERT(mismatchedFieldName);
440 if (mismatchedFieldName->empty())
441 {
442 *mismatchedFieldName = parentName;
443 }
444 else
445 {
446 std::ostringstream stream;
447 stream << parentName << "." << *mismatchedFieldName;
448 *mismatchedFieldName = stream.str();
449 }
450}

452const char *GetLinkMismatchErrorString(LinkMismatchError linkError)
453{
454 switch (linkError)
455 {
456 case LinkMismatchError::TYPE_MISMATCH:
457 return "Type";
458 case LinkMismatchError::ARRAY_SIZE_MISMATCH:
459 return "Array size";
460 case LinkMismatchError::PRECISION_MISMATCH:
461 return "Precision";
462 case LinkMismatchError::STRUCT_NAME_MISMATCH:
463 return "Structure name";
464 case LinkMismatchError::FIELD_NUMBER_MISMATCH:
465 return "Field number";
466 case LinkMismatchError::FIELD_NAME_MISMATCH:
467 return "Field name";
468
469 case LinkMismatchError::INTERPOLATION_TYPE_MISMATCH:
470 return "Interpolation type";
471 case LinkMismatchError::INVARIANCE_MISMATCH:
472 return "Invariance";
473
474 case LinkMismatchError::BINDING_MISMATCH:
475 return "Binding layout qualifier";
476 case LinkMismatchError::LOCATION_MISMATCH:
477 return "Location layout qualifier";
478 case LinkMismatchError::OFFSET_MISMATCH:
479 return "Offset layout qualifier";
480 case LinkMismatchError::INSTANCE_NAME_MISMATCH:
481 return "Instance name qualifier";
482 case LinkMismatchError::FORMAT_MISMATCH:
483 return "Format qualifier";
484
485 case LinkMismatchError::LAYOUT_QUALIFIER_MISMATCH:
486 return "Layout qualifier";
487 case LinkMismatchError::MATRIX_PACKING_MISMATCH:
488 return "Matrix Packing";
489 default:
490 UNREACHABLE();
491 return "";
492 }

494
495LinkMismatchError LinkValidateInterfaceBlockFields(const sh::ShaderVariable &blockField1,
496 const sh::ShaderVariable &blockField2,
497 bool webglCompatibility,
498 std::string *mismatchedBlockFieldName)
499{
500 if (blockField1.name != blockField2.name)
501 {
502 return LinkMismatchError::FIELD_NAME_MISMATCH;
503 }
504
505 // If webgl, validate precision of UBO fields, otherwise don't. See Khronos bug 10287.
506 LinkMismatchError linkError = Program::LinkValidateVariablesBase(
507 blockField1, blockField2, webglCompatibility, true, mismatchedBlockFieldName);
508 if (linkError != LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH)
509 {
510 AddParentPrefix(blockField1.name, mismatchedBlockFieldName);
511 return linkError;
512 }
513
514 if (blockField1.isRowMajorLayout != blockField2.isRowMajorLayout)
515 {
516 AddParentPrefix(blockField1.name, mismatchedBlockFieldName);
517 return LinkMismatchError::MATRIX_PACKING_MISMATCH;
518 }
519
520 return LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH;
521}
522
523LinkMismatchError AreMatchingInterfaceBlocks(const sh::InterfaceBlock &interfaceBlock1,
524 const sh::InterfaceBlock &interfaceBlock2,
525 bool webglCompatibility,
526 std::string *mismatchedBlockFieldName)
527{
528 // validate blocks for the same member types
529 if (interfaceBlock1.fields.size() != interfaceBlock2.fields.size())
530 {
531 return LinkMismatchError::FIELD_NUMBER_MISMATCH;
532 }
533 if (interfaceBlock1.arraySize != interfaceBlock2.arraySize)
534 {
535 return LinkMismatchError::ARRAY_SIZE_MISMATCH;
536 }
537 if (interfaceBlock1.layout != interfaceBlock2.layout ||
538 interfaceBlock1.binding != interfaceBlock2.binding)
539 {
540 return LinkMismatchError::LAYOUT_QUALIFIER_MISMATCH;
541 }
542 if (interfaceBlock1.instanceName.empty() != interfaceBlock2.instanceName.empty())
543 {
544 return LinkMismatchError::INSTANCE_NAME_MISMATCH;
545 }
546 const unsigned int numBlockMembers = static_cast<unsigned int>(interfaceBlock1.fields.size());
547 for (unsigned int blockMemberIndex = 0; blockMemberIndex < numBlockMembers; blockMemberIndex++)
548 {
549 const sh::ShaderVariable &member1 = interfaceBlock1.fields[blockMemberIndex];
550 const sh::ShaderVariable &member2 = interfaceBlock2.fields[blockMemberIndex];
551
552 LinkMismatchError linkError = LinkValidateInterfaceBlockFields(
553 member1, member2, webglCompatibility, mismatchedBlockFieldName);
554 if (linkError != LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH)
555 {
556 return linkError;
557 }
558 }
559 return LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH;
560}

562using ShaderInterfaceBlock = std::pair<ShaderType, const sh::InterfaceBlock *>;
563using InterfaceBlockMap = std::map<std::string, ShaderInterfaceBlock>;
564
565void InitializeInterfaceBlockMap(const std::vector<sh::InterfaceBlock> &interfaceBlocks,
566 ShaderType shaderType,
567 InterfaceBlockMap *linkedInterfaceBlocks)
568{
569 ASSERT(linkedInterfaceBlocks);
570
571 for (const sh::InterfaceBlock &interfaceBlock : interfaceBlocks)
572 {
573 (*linkedInterfaceBlocks)[interfaceBlock.name] = std::make_pair(shaderType, &interfaceBlock);
574 }
575}
576
577bool ValidateGraphicsInterfaceBlocksPerShader(
578 const std::vector<sh::InterfaceBlock> &interfaceBlocksToLink,
579 ShaderType shaderType,
580 bool webglCompatibility,
581 InterfaceBlockMap *linkedBlocks,
582 InfoLog &infoLog)
583{
584 ASSERT(linkedBlocks);
585
586 for (const sh::InterfaceBlock &block : interfaceBlocksToLink)
587 {
588 const auto &entry = linkedBlocks->find(block.name);
589 if (entry != linkedBlocks->end())
590 {
591 const sh::InterfaceBlock &linkedBlock = *(entry->second.second);
592 std::string mismatchedStructFieldName;
593 LinkMismatchError linkError = AreMatchingInterfaceBlocks(
594 block, linkedBlock, webglCompatibility, &mismatchedStructFieldName);
595 if (linkError != LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH)
596 {
597 LogLinkMismatch(infoLog, block.name, GetInterfaceBlockTypeString(block.blockType),
598 linkError, mismatchedStructFieldName, entry->second.first,
599 shaderType);
600 return false;
601 }
602 }
603 else
604 {
605 (*linkedBlocks)[block.name] = std::make_pair(shaderType, &block);
606 }
607 }
608
609 return true;
610}
611
612bool ValidateInterfaceBlocksMatch(
613 GLuint numShadersHasInterfaceBlocks,
614 const ShaderMap<const std::vector<sh::InterfaceBlock> *> &shaderInterfaceBlocks,
615 InfoLog &infoLog,
616 bool webglCompatibility)
617{
618 if (numShadersHasInterfaceBlocks < 2u)
619 {
620 return true;
621 }
622
623 ASSERT(!shaderInterfaceBlocks[ShaderType::Compute]);
624
625 // Check that interface blocks defined in the graphics shaders are identical
626
627 InterfaceBlockMap linkedInterfaceBlocks;
628
629 bool interfaceBlockMapInitialized = false;
630 for (ShaderType shaderType : kAllGraphicsShaderTypes)
631 {
632 if (!shaderInterfaceBlocks[shaderType])
633 {
634 continue;
635 }
636
637 if (!interfaceBlockMapInitialized)
638 {
639 InitializeInterfaceBlockMap(*shaderInterfaceBlocks[shaderType], shaderType,
640 &linkedInterfaceBlocks);
641 interfaceBlockMapInitialized = true;
642 }
643 else if (!ValidateGraphicsInterfaceBlocksPerShader(*shaderInterfaceBlocks[shaderType],
644 shaderType, webglCompatibility,
645 &linkedInterfaceBlocks, infoLog))
646 {
647 return false;
648 }
649 }
650
651 return true;
652}

654void WriteShaderVariableBuffer(BinaryOutputStream *stream, const ShaderVariableBuffer &var)
655{
656 stream->writeInt(var.binding);
657 stream->writeInt(var.dataSize);
658
659 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
660 {
661 stream->writeBool(var.isActive(shaderType));
662 }
663
664 stream->writeInt(var.memberIndexes.size());
665 for (unsigned int memberCounterIndex : var.memberIndexes)
666 {
667 stream->writeInt(memberCounterIndex);
668 }
669}
670
671void LoadShaderVariableBuffer(BinaryInputStream *stream, ShaderVariableBuffer *var)
672{
673 var->binding = stream->readInt<int>();
674 var->dataSize = stream->readInt<unsigned int>();
675
676 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
677 {
678 var->setActive(shaderType, stream->readBool());
679 }
680
681 size_t numMembers = stream->readInt<size_t>();
682 for (size_t blockMemberIndex = 0; blockMemberIndex < numMembers; blockMemberIndex++)
683 {
684 var->memberIndexes.push_back(stream->readInt<unsigned int>());
685 }
686}
687
688void WriteBufferVariable(BinaryOutputStream *stream, const BufferVariable &var)
689{
690 WriteShaderVar(stream, var);
691
692 stream->writeInt(var.bufferIndex);
693 WriteBlockMemberInfo(stream, var.blockInfo);
694 stream->writeInt(var.topLevelArraySize);
695
696 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
697 {
698 stream->writeBool(var.isActive(shaderType));
699 }
700}
701
702void LoadBufferVariable(BinaryInputStream *stream, BufferVariable *var)
703{
704 LoadShaderVar(stream, var);
705
706 var->bufferIndex = stream->readInt<int>();
707 LoadBlockMemberInfo(stream, &var->blockInfo);
708 var->topLevelArraySize = stream->readInt<int>();
709
710 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
711 {
712 var->setActive(shaderType, stream->readBool());
713 }
714}
715
716void WriteInterfaceBlock(BinaryOutputStream *stream, const InterfaceBlock &block)
717{
718 stream->writeString(block.name);
719 stream->writeString(block.mappedName);
720 stream->writeBool(block.isArray);
721 stream->writeInt(block.arrayElement);
722
723 WriteShaderVariableBuffer(stream, block);
724}
725
726void LoadInterfaceBlock(BinaryInputStream *stream, InterfaceBlock *block)
727{
728 block->name = stream->readString();
729 block->mappedName = stream->readString();
730 block->isArray = stream->readBool();
731 block->arrayElement = stream->readInt<unsigned int>();
732
733 LoadShaderVariableBuffer(stream, block);
734}

749// InfoLog implementation.
750InfoLog::InfoLog() : mLazyStream(nullptr) {}
751
752InfoLog::~InfoLog() {}
753
754size_t InfoLog::getLength() const
755{
756 if (!mLazyStream)
757 {
758 return 0;
759 }
760
761 const std::string &logString = mLazyStream->str();
762 return logString.empty() ? 0 : logString.length() + 1;
763}
764
765void InfoLog::getLog(GLsizei bufSize, GLsizei *length, char *infoLog) const
766{
767 size_t index = 0;
768
769 if (bufSize > 0)
770 {
771 const std::string logString(str());
772
773 if (!logString.empty())
774 {
775 index = std::min(static_cast<size_t>(bufSize) - 1, logString.length());
776 memcpy(infoLog, logString.c_str(), index);
777 }
778
779 infoLog[index] = '\0';
780 }
781
782 if (length)
783 {
784 *length = static_cast<GLsizei>(index);
785 }
786}

788// append a santized message to the program info log.
789// The D3D compiler includes a fake file path in some of the warning or error
790// messages, so lets remove all occurrences of this fake file path from the log.
791void InfoLog::appendSanitized(const char *message)
792{
793 ensureInitialized();
794
795 std::string msg(message);
796
797 size_t found;
798 do
799 {
800 found = msg.find(g_fakepath);
801 if (found != std::string::npos)
802 {
803 msg.erase(found, strlen(g_fakepath));
804 }
805 } while (found != std::string::npos);
806
807 *mLazyStream << message << std::endl;
808}
809
810void InfoLog::reset()
811{
812 if (mLazyStream)
813 {
814 mLazyStream.reset(nullptr);
815 }
816}
817
818bool InfoLog::empty() const
819{
820 if (!mLazyStream)
821 {
822 return true;
823 }
824
825 return mLazyStream->rdbuf()->in_avail() == 0;
826}

828void LogLinkMismatch(InfoLog &infoLog,
829 const std::string &variableName,
830 const char *variableType,
831 LinkMismatchError linkError,
832 const std::string &mismatchedStructOrBlockFieldName,
833 ShaderType shaderType1,
834 ShaderType shaderType2)
835{
836 std::ostringstream stream;
837 stream << GetLinkMismatchErrorString(linkError) << "s of " << variableType << " '"
838 << variableName;
839
840 if (!mismatchedStructOrBlockFieldName.empty())
841 {
842 stream << "' member '" << variableName << "." << mismatchedStructOrBlockFieldName;
843 }
844
845 stream << "' differ between " << GetShaderTypeString(shaderType1) << " and "
846 << GetShaderTypeString(shaderType2) << " shaders.";

848 infoLog << stream.str();
849}

911 var->offset = stream->readInt<int>();
912 var->readonly = stream->readBool();
913 var->writeonly = stream->readBool();

969ProgramAliasedBindings::ProgramAliasedBindings() {}

972
973void ProgramAliasedBindings::bindLocation(GLuint index, const std::string &name)
974{
975 mBindings[name] = ProgramBinding(index);
976
977 // EXT_blend_func_extended spec: "If it specifies the base name of an array,
978 // it identifies the resources associated with the first element of the array."
979 //
980 // Normalize array bindings so that "name" and "name[0]" map to the same entry.
981 // If this binding is of the form "name[0]", then mark the "name" binding as
982 // aliased but do not update it yet in case "name" is not actually an array.
983 size_t nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex;
984 unsigned int arrayIndex = ParseArrayIndex(name, &nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex);
985 if (arrayIndex == 0)
986 {
987 std::string baseName = name.substr(0u, nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex);
988 auto iter = mBindings.find(baseName);
989 if (iter != mBindings.end())
990 {
991 iter->second.aliased = true;
992 }
993 }
994}
995
996int ProgramAliasedBindings::getBindingByName(const std::string &name) const
997{
998 auto iter = mBindings.find(name);
999 return (iter != mBindings.end()) ? iter->second.location : -1;
1000}
1001
1002int ProgramAliasedBindings::getBindingByLocation(GLuint location) const
1003{
1004 for (const auto &iter : mBindings)
1005 {
1006 if (iter.second.location == location)
1007 {
1008 return iter.second.location;
1009 }
1010 }
1011 return -1;
1012}
1013
1014int ProgramAliasedBindings::getBinding(const sh::ShaderVariable &variable) const
1015{
1016 const std::string &name = variable.name;
1017
1018 // Check with the normalized array name if applicable.
1019 if (variable.isArray())
1020 {
1021 size_t nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex;
1022 unsigned int arrayIndex = ParseArrayIndex(name, &nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex);
1023 if (arrayIndex == 0)
1024 {
1025 std::string baseName = name.substr(0u, nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex);
1026 auto iter = mBindings.find(baseName);
1027 // If "name" exists and is not aliased, that means it was modified more
1028 // recently than its "name[0]" form and should be used instead of that.
1029 if (iter != mBindings.end() && !iter->second.aliased)
1030 {
1031 return iter->second.location;
1032 }
1033 }
1034 else if (arrayIndex == GL_INVALID_INDEX)
1035 {
1036 auto iter = mBindings.find(variable.name);
1037 // If "name" exists and is not aliased, that means it was modified more
1038 // recently than its "name[0]" form and should be used instead of that.
1039 if (iter != mBindings.end() && !iter->second.aliased)
1040 {
1041 return iter->second.location;
1042 }
1043 // The base name was aliased, so use the name with the array notation.
1044 return getBindingByName(name + "[0]");
1045 }
1046 }
1047
1048 return getBindingByName(name);
1049}

1052{
1053 return mBindings.begin();
1054}
1055
1056ProgramAliasedBindings::const_iterator ProgramAliasedBindings::end() const
1057{
1058 return mBindings.end();

1284void Program::attachShader(const Context *context, Shader *shader)
1285{
1286 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
1287 ShaderType shaderType = shader->getType();
1288 ASSERT(shaderType != ShaderType::InvalidEnum);
1289
1290 // Since detachShader doesn't actually detach anymore, we need to do that work when attaching a
1291 // new shader to make sure we don't lose track of it and free the resources.
1292 if (mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType])
1293 {
1294 mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType]->release(context);
1295 mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType] = nullptr;
1296 mState.mAttachedShadersMarkedForDetach[shaderType] = false;
1297 }
1298
1299 mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType] = shader;
1300 mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType]->addRef();
1301}
1302
1303void Program::detachShader(const Context *context, Shader *shader)
1304{
1305 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
1306 ShaderType shaderType = shader->getType();
1307 ASSERT(shaderType != ShaderType::InvalidEnum);
1308
1309 ASSERT(mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType] == shader);
1310
1311 if (isSeparable())
1312 {
1313 // Don't actually detach the shader since we still need it in case this
1314 // Program is part of a Program Pipeline Object. Instead, leave a mark
1315 // that indicates we intended to.
1316 mState.mAttachedShadersMarkedForDetach[shaderType] = true;
1317 return;
1318 }
1319
1320 shader->release(context);
1321 mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType] = nullptr;
1322 mState.mAttachedShadersMarkedForDetach[shaderType] = false;
1323}

1368angle::Result Program::linkMergedVaryings(const Context *context,
1369 const ProgramExecutable &executable,
1370 const ProgramMergedVaryings &mergedVaryings)
1371{
1372 ShaderType tfStage =
1373 mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Geometry] ? ShaderType::Geometry : ShaderType::Vertex;
1374 InfoLog &infoLog = getExecutable().getInfoLog();
1375
1376 if (!linkValidateTransformFeedback(context->getClientVersion(), infoLog, mergedVaryings,
1377 tfStage, context->getCaps()))
1378 {
1379 return angle::Result::Stop;
1380 }
1381
1382 if (!executable.mResources->varyingPacking.collectAndPackUserVaryings(
1383 infoLog, mergedVaryings, mState.getTransformFeedbackVaryingNames(), isSeparable()))
1384 {
1385 return angle::Result::Stop;
1386 }
1387
1388 gatherTransformFeedbackVaryings(mergedVaryings, tfStage);
1389 mState.updateTransformFeedbackStrides();
1390
1391 return angle::Result::Continue;
1392}
1393
1394angle::Result Program::link(const Context *context)
1395{
1396 angle::Result result = linkImpl(context);
1397
1398 // Avoid having two ProgramExecutables if the link failed and the Program had successfully
1399 // linked previously.
1400 if (mLinkingState && mLinkingState->linkedExecutable)
1401 {
1402 mState.mExecutable = mLinkingState->linkedExecutable;
1403 }
1404
1405 return result;
1406}
1407
1408// The attached shaders are checked for linking errors by matching up their variables.
1409// Uniform, input and output variables get collected.
1410// The code gets compiled into binaries.
1411angle::Result Program::linkImpl(const Context *context)
1412{
1413 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
1414 // Don't make any local variables pointing to anything within the ProgramExecutable, since
1415 // unlink() could make a new ProgramExecutable making any references/pointers invalid.
1416 const auto &data = context->getState();
1417 auto *platform = ANGLEPlatformCurrent();
1418 double startTime = platform->currentTime(platform);
1419
1420 // Unlink the program, but do not clear the validation-related caching yet, since we can still
1421 // use the previously linked program if linking the shaders fails.
1422 mLinked = false;
1423
1424 mState.mExecutable->getInfoLog().reset();
1425
1426 // Validate we have properly attached shaders before checking the cache.
1427 if (!linkValidateShaders(mState.mExecutable->getInfoLog()))
1428 {
1429 return angle::Result::Continue;
1430 }
1431
1432 egl::BlobCache::Key programHash = {0};
1433 MemoryProgramCache *cache = context->getMemoryProgramCache();
1434
1435 // TODO: http://anglebug.com/4530: Enable program caching for separable programs
1436 if (cache && !isSeparable())
1437 {
1438 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> cacheLock(context->getProgramCacheMutex());
1439 angle::Result cacheResult = cache->getProgram(context, this, &programHash);
1440 ANGLE_TRY(cacheResult);
1441
1442 // Check explicitly for Continue, Incomplete means a cache miss
1443 if (cacheResult == angle::Result::Continue)
1444 {
1445 // Succeeded in loading the binaries in the front-end, back end may still be loading
1446 // asynchronously
1447 double delta = platform->currentTime(platform) - startTime;
1448 int us = static_cast<int>(delta * 1000000.0);
1449 ANGLE_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS("GPU.ANGLE.ProgramCache.ProgramCacheHitTimeUS", us);
1450 return angle::Result::Continue;
1451 }
1452 }
1453
1454 // Cache load failed, fall through to normal linking.
1455 unlink();
1456 InfoLog &infoLog = mState.mExecutable->getInfoLog();
1457
1458 // Re-link shaders after the unlink call.
1459 bool result = linkValidateShaders(infoLog);
1460 ASSERT(result);
1461
1462 ProgramMergedVaryings mergedVaryings;
1463
1464 if (mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Compute])
1465 {
1466 mState.mExecutable->mResources.reset(new ProgramLinkedResources(
1467 0, PackMode::ANGLE_RELAXED, &mState.mExecutable->mUniformBlocks,
1468 &mState.mExecutable->mUniforms, &mState.mExecutable->mComputeShaderStorageBlocks,
1469 &mState.mBufferVariables, &mState.mExecutable->mAtomicCounterBuffers));
1470
1471 GLuint combinedImageUniforms = 0u;
1472 if (!linkUniforms(context->getCaps(), context->getClientVersion(), infoLog,
1473 mState.mUniformLocationBindings, &combinedImageUniforms,
1474 &mState.mExecutable->getResources().unusedUniforms))
1475 {
1476 return angle::Result::Continue;
1477 }
1478
1479 GLuint combinedShaderStorageBlocks = 0u;
1480 if (!linkInterfaceBlocks(context->getCaps(), context->getClientVersion(),
1481 context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility, infoLog,
1482 &combinedShaderStorageBlocks))
1483 {
1484 return angle::Result::Continue;
1485 }
1486
1487 // [OpenGL ES 3.1] Chapter 8.22 Page 203:
1488 // A link error will be generated if the sum of the number of active image uniforms used in
1489 // all shaders, the number of active shader storage blocks, and the number of active
1490 // fragment shader outputs exceeds the implementation-dependent value of
1491 // MAX_COMBINED_SHADER_OUTPUT_RESOURCES.
1492 if (combinedImageUniforms + combinedShaderStorageBlocks >
1493 static_cast<GLuint>(context->getCaps().maxCombinedShaderOutputResources))
1494 {
1495 infoLog
1496 << "The sum of the number of active image uniforms, active shader storage blocks "
1497 "and active fragment shader outputs exceeds "
1498 "MAX_COMBINED_SHADER_OUTPUT_RESOURCES ("
1499 << context->getCaps().maxCombinedShaderOutputResources << ")";
1500 return angle::Result::Continue;
1501 }
1502
1503 InitUniformBlockLinker(mState, &mState.mExecutable->getResources().uniformBlockLinker);
1504 InitShaderStorageBlockLinker(mState,
1505 &mState.mExecutable->getResources().shaderStorageBlockLinker);
1506 }
1507 else
1508 {
1509 // Map the varyings to the register file
1510 // In WebGL, we use a slightly different handling for packing variables.
1511 gl::PackMode packMode = PackMode::ANGLE_RELAXED;
1512 if (data.getLimitations().noFlexibleVaryingPacking)
1513 {
1514 // D3D9 pack mode is strictly more strict than WebGL, so takes priority.
1515 packMode = PackMode::ANGLE_NON_CONFORMANT_D3D9;
1516 }
1517 else if (data.getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
1518 {
1519 packMode = PackMode::WEBGL_STRICT;
1520 }
1521
1522 mState.mExecutable->mResources.reset(new ProgramLinkedResources(
1523 static_cast<GLuint>(data.getCaps().maxVaryingVectors), packMode,
1524 &mState.mExecutable->mUniformBlocks, &mState.mExecutable->mUniforms,
1525 &mState.mExecutable->mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks, &mState.mBufferVariables,
1526 &mState.mExecutable->mAtomicCounterBuffers));
1527
1528 if (!linkAttributes(context, infoLog))
1529 {
1530 return angle::Result::Continue;
1531 }
1532
1533 if (!linkVaryings(infoLog))
1534 {
1535 return angle::Result::Continue;
1536 }
1537
1538 GLuint combinedImageUniforms = 0u;
1539 if (!linkUniforms(context->getCaps(), context->getClientVersion(), infoLog,
1540 mState.mUniformLocationBindings, &combinedImageUniforms,
1541 &mState.mExecutable->getResources().unusedUniforms))
1542 {
1543 return angle::Result::Continue;
1544 }
1545
1546 GLuint combinedShaderStorageBlocks = 0u;
1547 if (!linkInterfaceBlocks(context->getCaps(), context->getClientVersion(),
1548 context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility, infoLog,
1549 &combinedShaderStorageBlocks))
1550 {
1551 return angle::Result::Continue;
1552 }
1553
1554 gl::ShaderMap<const gl::ProgramState *> programStates;
1555 fillProgramStateMap(&programStates);
1556 if (!mState.mExecutable->linkValidateGlobalNames(infoLog, programStates))
1557 {
1558 return angle::Result::Continue;
1559 }
1560
1561 if (!linkOutputVariables(context->getCaps(), context->getExtensions(),
1562 context->getClientVersion(), combinedImageUniforms,
1563 combinedShaderStorageBlocks))
1564 {
1565 return angle::Result::Continue;
1566 }
1567
1568 gl::Shader *vertexShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Vertex];
1569 if (vertexShader)
1570 {
1571 mState.mNumViews = vertexShader->getNumViews();
1572 }
1573
1574 gl::Shader *fragmentShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Fragment];
1575 if (fragmentShader)
1576 {
1577 mState.mEarlyFramentTestsOptimization =
1578 fragmentShader->hasEarlyFragmentTestsOptimization();
1579 }
1580
1581 InitUniformBlockLinker(mState, &mState.mExecutable->getResources().uniformBlockLinker);
1582 InitShaderStorageBlockLinker(mState,
1583 &mState.mExecutable->getResources().shaderStorageBlockLinker);
1584
1585 ProgramPipeline *programPipeline = context->getState().getProgramPipeline();
1586 if (programPipeline && programPipeline->usesShaderProgram(id()))
1587 {
1588 mergedVaryings = context->getState().getProgramPipeline()->getMergedVaryings();
1589 }
1590 else
1591 {
1592 mergedVaryings = getMergedVaryings();
1593 }
1594 ANGLE_TRY(linkMergedVaryings(context, *mState.mExecutable, mergedVaryings));
1595 }
1596
1597 updateLinkedShaderStages();
1598
1599 mLinkingState.reset(new LinkingState());
1600 mLinkingState->linkingFromBinary = false;
1601 mLinkingState->programHash = programHash;
1602 mLinkingState->linkEvent =
1603 mProgram->link(context, mState.mExecutable->getResources(), infoLog, mergedVaryings);
1604
1605 // Must be after mProgram->link() to avoid misleading the linker about output variables.
1606 mState.updateProgramInterfaceInputs();
1607 mState.updateProgramInterfaceOutputs();
1608
1609 // Linking has succeeded, so we need to save some information that may get overwritten by a
1610 // later linkProgram() that could fail.
1611 if (mState.mSeparable)
1612 {
1613 mState.mExecutable->saveLinkedStateInfo(mState);
1614 mLinkingState->linkedExecutable = mState.mExecutable;
1615 }
1616
1617 return angle::Result::Continue;
1618}
1619
1620bool Program::isLinking() const
1621{
1622 return (mLinkingState.get() && mLinkingState->linkEvent &&
1623 mLinkingState->linkEvent->isLinking());
1624}
1625
1626void Program::resolveLinkImpl(const Context *context)
1627{
1628 ASSERT(mLinkingState.get());
1629
1630 angle::Result result = mLinkingState->linkEvent->wait(context);
1631
1632 mLinked = result == angle::Result::Continue;
1633 std::unique_ptr<LinkingState> linkingState = std::move(mLinkingState);
1634 if (!mLinked)
1635 {
1636 return;
1637 }
1638
1639 if (linkingState->linkingFromBinary)
1640 {
1641 // All internal Program state is already loaded from the binary.
1642 return;
1643 }
1644
1645 initInterfaceBlockBindings();
1646
1647 // According to GLES 3.0/3.1 spec for LinkProgram and UseProgram,
1648 // Only successfully linked program can replace the executables.
1649 ASSERT(mLinked);
1650
1651 // Mark implementation-specific unreferenced uniforms as ignored.
1652 std::vector<ImageBinding> *imageBindings = getExecutable().getImageBindings();
1653 mProgram->markUnusedUniformLocations(&mState.mUniformLocations,
1654 &mState.mExecutable->mSamplerBindings, imageBindings);
1655
1656 // Must be called after markUnusedUniformLocations.
1657 postResolveLink(context);
1658
1659 // Save to the program cache.
1660 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> cacheLock(context->getProgramCacheMutex());
1661 MemoryProgramCache *cache = context->getMemoryProgramCache();
1662 // TODO: http://anglebug.com/4530: Enable program caching for separable programs
1663 if (cache && !isSeparable() &&
1664 (mState.mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings.empty() ||
1665 !context->getFrontendFeatures().disableProgramCachingForTransformFeedback.enabled))
1666 {
1667 if (cache->putProgram(linkingState->programHash, context, this) == angle::Result::Stop)
1668 {
1669 // Don't fail linking if putting the program binary into the cache fails, the program is
1670 // still usable.
1671 WARN() << "Failed to save linked program to memory program cache.";
1672 }
1673 }
1674}

1676void Program::updateLinkedShaderStages()
1677{
1678 mState.mExecutable->resetLinkedShaderStages();
1679
1680 for (const Shader *shader : mState.mAttachedShaders)
1681 {
1682 if (shader)
1683 {
1684 mState.mExecutable->setLinkedShaderStages(shader->getType());
1685 }
1686 }
1687
1688 if (mState.mExecutable->hasLinkedShaderStage(ShaderType::Compute))
1689 {
1690 mState.mExecutable->setIsCompute(true);
1691 }
1692 else
1693 {
1694 mState.mExecutable->setIsCompute(false);
1695 }
1696}

1698void ProgramState::updateTransformFeedbackStrides()
1699{
1700 if (mExecutable->mTransformFeedbackBufferMode == GL_INTERLEAVED_ATTRIBS)
1701 {
1702 mExecutable->mTransformFeedbackStrides.resize(1);
1703 size_t totalSize = 0;
1704 for (const TransformFeedbackVarying &varying :
1705 mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings)
1706 {
1707 totalSize += varying.size() * VariableExternalSize(varying.type);
1708 }
1709 mExecutable->mTransformFeedbackStrides[0] = static_cast<GLsizei>(totalSize);
1710 }
1711 else
1712 {
1713 mExecutable->mTransformFeedbackStrides.resize(
1714 mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings.size());
1715 for (size_t i = 0; i < mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings.size(); i++)
1716 {
1717 TransformFeedbackVarying &varying = mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings[i];
1718 mExecutable->mTransformFeedbackStrides[i] =
1719 static_cast<GLsizei>(varying.size() * VariableExternalSize(varying.type));
1720 }
1721 }
1722}

1729
1730void ProgramState::updateProgramInterfaceInputs()
1731{
1732 const ShaderType firstAttachedShaderType = getFirstAttachedShaderStageType();
1733
1734 if (firstAttachedShaderType == ShaderType::Vertex)
1735 {
1736 // Vertex attributes are already what we need, so nothing to do
1737 return;
1738 }
1739
1740 Shader *shader = getAttachedShader(firstAttachedShaderType);
1741 ASSERT(shader);
1742
1743 // Copy over each input varying, since the Shader could go away
1744 if (shader->getType() == ShaderType::Compute)
1745 {
1746 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &attribute : shader->getAllAttributes())
1747 {
1748 // Compute Shaders have the following built-in input variables.
1749 //
1750 // in uvec3 gl_NumWorkGroups;
1751 // in uvec3 gl_WorkGroupID;
1752 // in uvec3 gl_LocalInvocationID;
1753 // in uvec3 gl_GlobalInvocationID;
1754 // in uint gl_LocalInvocationIndex;
1755 // They are all vecs or uints, so no special handling is required.
1756 mExecutable->mProgramInputs.emplace_back(attribute);
1757 }
1758 }
1759 else if (shader->getType() == ShaderType::Fragment)
1760 {
1761 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : shader->getInputVaryings())
1762 {
1763 if (varying.isStruct())
1764 {
1765 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &field : varying.fields)
1766 {
1767 sh::ShaderVariable fieldVarying = sh::ShaderVariable(field);
1768 fieldVarying.location = varying.location;
1769 fieldVarying.name = varying.name + "." + field.name;
1770 mExecutable->mProgramInputs.emplace_back(fieldVarying);
1771 }
1772 }
1773 else
1774 {
1775 mExecutable->mProgramInputs.emplace_back(varying);
1776 }
1777 }
1778 }
1779}
1780
1781void ProgramState::updateProgramInterfaceOutputs()
1782{
1783 const ShaderType lastAttachedShaderType = getLastAttachedShaderStageType();
1784
1785 if (lastAttachedShaderType == ShaderType::Fragment)
1786 {
1787 // Fragment outputs are already what we need, so nothing to do
1788 return;
1789 }
1790 if (lastAttachedShaderType == ShaderType::Compute)
1791 {
1792 // If the program only contains a Compute Shader, then there are no user-defined outputs.
1793 return;
1794 }
1795
1796 Shader *shader = getAttachedShader(lastAttachedShaderType);
1797 ASSERT(shader);
1798
1799 // Copy over each output varying, since the Shader could go away
1800 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : shader->getOutputVaryings())
1801 {
1802 if (varying.isStruct())
1803 {
1804 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &field : varying.fields)
1805 {
1806 sh::ShaderVariable fieldVarying = sh::ShaderVariable(field);
1807 fieldVarying.location = varying.location;
1808 fieldVarying.name = varying.name + "." + field.name;
1809 mExecutable->mOutputVariables.emplace_back(fieldVarying);
1810 }
1811 }
1812 else
1813 {
1814 mExecutable->mOutputVariables.emplace_back(varying);
1815 }
1816 }
1817}

1819// Returns the program object to an unlinked state, before re-linking, or at destruction
1820void Program::unlink()
1821{
1822 if (mLinkingState && mLinkingState->linkedExecutable)
1823 {
1824 // The new ProgramExecutable that we'll attempt to link with needs to start from a copy of
1825 // the last successfully linked ProgramExecutable, so we don't lose any state information.
1826 mState.mExecutable.reset(new ProgramExecutable(*mLinkingState->linkedExecutable));
1827 }
1828 mState.mExecutable->reset();
1829
1830 mState.mUniformLocations.clear();
1831 mState.mBufferVariables.clear();
1832 mState.mActiveUniformBlockBindings.reset();
1833 mState.mSecondaryOutputLocations.clear();
1834 mState.mOutputVariableTypes.clear();
1835 mState.mDrawBufferTypeMask.reset();
1836 mState.mActiveOutputVariables.reset();
1837 mState.mComputeShaderLocalSize.fill(1);
1838 mState.mNumViews = -1;
1839 mState.mGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType = PrimitiveMode::Triangles;
1840 mState.mGeometryShaderOutputPrimitiveType = PrimitiveMode::TriangleStrip;
1841 mState.mGeometryShaderInvocations = 1;
1842 mState.mGeometryShaderMaxVertices = 0;
1843 mState.mDrawIDLocation = -1;
1844 mState.mBaseVertexLocation = -1;
1845 mState.mBaseInstanceLocation = -1;
1846 mState.mCachedBaseVertex = 0;
1847 mState.mCachedBaseInstance = 0;
1848 mState.mEarlyFramentTestsOptimization = false;
1849
1850 mValidated = false;
1851
1852 mLinked = false;
1853}
1854
1855angle::Result Program::loadBinary(const Context *context,
1856 GLenum binaryFormat,
1857 const void *binary,
1858 GLsizei length)
1859{
1860 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
1861 unlink();
1862 InfoLog &infoLog = mState.mExecutable->getInfoLog();
1863
1864#if ANGLE_PROGRAM_BINARY_LOAD != ANGLE_ENABLED
1865 return angle::Result::Continue;
1866#else
1867 ASSERT(binaryFormat == GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_ANGLE);
1868 if (binaryFormat != GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_ANGLE)
1869 {
1870 infoLog << "Invalid program binary format.";
1871 return angle::Result::Continue;
1872 }
1873
1874 BinaryInputStream stream(binary, length);
1875 ANGLE_TRY(deserialize(context, stream, infoLog));
1876
1877 // Currently we require the full shader text to compute the program hash.
1878 // We could also store the binary in the internal program cache.
1879
1880 for (size_t uniformBlockIndex = 0;
1881 uniformBlockIndex < mState.mExecutable->getActiveUniformBlockCount(); ++uniformBlockIndex)
1882 {
1883 mDirtyBits.set(uniformBlockIndex);
1884 }
1885
1886 // The rx::LinkEvent returned from ProgramImpl::load is a base class with multiple
1887 // implementations. In some implementations, a background thread is used to compile the
1888 // shaders. Any calls to the LinkEvent object, therefore, are racy and may interfere with
1889 // the operation.
1890
1891 // We do not want to call LinkEvent::wait because that will cause the background thread
1892 // to finish its task before returning, thus defeating the purpose of background compilation.
1893 // We need to defer waiting on background compilation until the very last minute when we
1894 // absolutely need the results, such as when the developer binds the program or queries
1895 // for the completion status.
1896
1897 // If load returns nullptr, we know for sure that the binary is not compatible with the backend.
1898 // The loaded binary could have been read from the on-disk shader cache and be corrupted or
1899 // serialized with different revision and subsystem id than the currently loaded backend.
1900 // Returning 'Incomplete' to the caller results in link happening using the original shader
1901 // sources.
1902 angle::Result result;
1903 std::unique_ptr<LinkingState> linkingState;
1904 std::unique_ptr<rx::LinkEvent> linkEvent = mProgram->load(context, &stream, infoLog);
1905 if (linkEvent)
1906 {
1907 linkingState = std::make_unique<LinkingState>();
1908 linkingState->linkingFromBinary = true;
1909 linkingState->linkEvent = std::move(linkEvent);
1910 result = angle::Result::Continue;
1911 }
1912 else
1913 {
1914 result = angle::Result::Incomplete;
1915 }
1916 mLinkingState = std::move(linkingState);
1917
1918 return result;
1919#endif // #if ANGLE_PROGRAM_BINARY_LOAD == ANGLE_ENABLED
1920}
1921
1922angle::Result Program::saveBinary(Context *context,
1923 GLenum *binaryFormat,
1924 void *binary,
1925 GLsizei bufSize,
1926 GLsizei *length) const
1927{
1928 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
1929 if (binaryFormat)
1930 {
1931 *binaryFormat = GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_ANGLE;
1932 }
1933
1934 angle::MemoryBuffer memoryBuf;
1935 ANGLE_TRY(serialize(context, &memoryBuf));
1936
1937 GLsizei streamLength = static_cast<GLsizei>(memoryBuf.size());
1938 const uint8_t *streamState = memoryBuf.data();
1939
1940 if (streamLength > bufSize)
1941 {
1942 if (length)
1943 {
1944 *length = 0;
1945 }
1946
1947 // TODO: This should be moved to the validation layer but computing the size of the binary
1948 // before saving it causes the save to happen twice. It may be possible to write the binary
1949 // to a separate buffer, validate sizes and then copy it.
1950 ANGLE_CHECK(context, false, "Insufficient buffer size", GL_INVALID_OPERATION);
1951 }
1952
1953 if (binary)
1954 {
1955 char *ptr = reinterpret_cast<char *>(binary);
1956
1957 memcpy(ptr, streamState, streamLength);
1958 ptr += streamLength;
1959
1960 ASSERT(ptr - streamLength == binary);
1961 }
1962
1963 if (length)
1964 {
1965 *length = streamLength;
1966 }
1967
1968 return angle::Result::Continue;
1969}
1970
1971GLint Program::getBinaryLength(Context *context) const
1972{
1973 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
1974 if (!mLinked)
1975 {
1976 return 0;
1977 }
1978
1979 GLint length;
1980 angle::Result result =
1981 saveBinary(context, nullptr, nullptr, std::numeric_limits<GLint>::max(), &length);
1982 if (result != angle::Result::Continue)
1983 {
1984 return 0;
1985 }
1986
1987 return length;
1988}

2458 GLsizei bufsize,
2459 GLsizei *length,
2460 GLint *size,
2461 GLenum *type,
2462 GLchar *name) const
2463{
2464 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
2465 if (mLinked)
2466 {
2467 // index must be smaller than getActiveUniformCount()

2920void Program::getUniformfv(const Context *context, UniformLocation location, GLfloat *v) const
2921{
2922 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
2923 const VariableLocation &uniformLocation = mState.getUniformLocations()[location.value];
2924 const LinkedUniform &uniform = mState.getUniforms()[uniformLocation.index];
2925
2926 if (uniform.isSampler())
2927 {
2928 *v = static_cast<GLfloat>(getSamplerUniformBinding(uniformLocation));
2929 return;
2930 }
2931 else if (uniform.isImage())
2932 {
2933 *v = static_cast<GLfloat>(getImageUniformBinding(uniformLocation));
2934 return;
2935 }
2936
2937 const GLenum nativeType = gl::VariableComponentType(uniform.type);
2938 if (nativeType == GL_FLOAT)
2939 {
2940 mProgram->getUniformfv(context, location.value, v);
2941 }
2942 else
2943 {
2944 getUniformInternal(context, v, location, nativeType, VariableComponentCount(uniform.type));
2945 }
2946}

2948void Program::getUniformiv(const Context *context, UniformLocation location, GLint *v) const
2949{
2950 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);

2952 const LinkedUniform &uniform = mState.getUniforms()[uniformLocation.index];
2953
2954 if (uniform.isSampler())
2955 {
2956 *v = static_cast<GLint>(getSamplerUniformBinding(uniformLocation));
2957 return;
2958 }
2959 else if (uniform.isImage())
2960 {
2961 *v = static_cast<GLint>(getImageUniformBinding(uniformLocation));
2962 return;
2963 }
2964
2965 const GLenum nativeType = gl::VariableComponentType(uniform.type);
2966 if (nativeType == GL_INT || nativeType == GL_BOOL)
2967 {

3031
3032bool Program::validateSamplersImpl(InfoLog *infoLog, const Caps &caps)
3033{
3034 const ProgramExecutable *executable = mState.mExecutable.get();
3035 ASSERT(!mLinkingState);
3036
3037 // if any two active samplers in a program are of different types, but refer to the same
3038 // texture image unit, and this is the current program, then ValidateProgram will fail, and
3039 // DrawArrays and DrawElements will issue the INVALID_OPERATION error.
3040 for (size_t textureUnit : executable->mActiveSamplersMask)
3041 {
3042 if (executable->mActiveSamplerTypes[textureUnit] == TextureType::InvalidEnum)
3043 {
3044 if (infoLog)
3045 {
3046 (*infoLog) << "Samplers of conflicting types refer to the same texture "
3047 "image unit ("

3250
3251bool Program::linkValidateShaders(InfoLog &infoLog)
3252{
3253 Shader *vertexShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Vertex];
3254 Shader *fragmentShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Fragment];
3255 Shader *computeShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Compute];
3256 Shader *geometryShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Geometry];
3257
3258 bool isComputeShaderAttached = (computeShader != nullptr);
3259 bool isGraphicsShaderAttached =
3260 (vertexShader != nullptr || fragmentShader != nullptr || geometryShader != nullptr);
3261 // Check whether we both have a compute and non-compute shaders attached.
3262 // If there are of both types attached, then linking should fail.
3263 // OpenGL ES 3.10, 7.3 Program Objects, under LinkProgram
3264 if (isComputeShaderAttached == true && isGraphicsShaderAttached == true)
3265 {
3266 infoLog << "Both compute and graphics shaders are attached to the same program.";
3267 return false;
3268 }
3269
3270 if (computeShader)
3271 {
3272 if (!computeShader->isCompiled())
3273 {
3274 infoLog << "Attached compute shader is not compiled.";
3275 return false;
3276 }
3277 ASSERT(computeShader->getType() == ShaderType::Compute);
3278
3279 mState.mComputeShaderLocalSize = computeShader->getWorkGroupSize();
3280
3281 // GLSL ES 3.10, 4.4.1.1 Compute Shader Inputs
3282 // If the work group size is not specified, a link time error should occur.
3283 if (!mState.mComputeShaderLocalSize.isDeclared())
3284 {
3285 infoLog << "Work group size is not specified.";
3286 return false;
3287 }
3288 }
3289 else
3290 {
3291 if (isSeparable())
3292 {
3293 if (!fragmentShader && !vertexShader)
3294 {
3295 infoLog << "No compiled shaders.";
3296 return false;
3297 }
3298
3299 ASSERT(!fragmentShader || fragmentShader->getType() == ShaderType::Fragment);
3300 if (fragmentShader && !fragmentShader->isCompiled())
3301 {
3302 infoLog << "Fragment shader is not compiled.";
3303 return false;
3304 }
3305
3306 ASSERT(!vertexShader || vertexShader->getType() == ShaderType::Vertex);
3307 if (vertexShader && !vertexShader->isCompiled())
3308 {
3309 infoLog << "Vertex shader is not compiled.";
3310 return false;
3311 }
3312 }
3313 else
3314 {
3315 if (!fragmentShader || !fragmentShader->isCompiled())
3316 {
3317 infoLog
3318 << "No compiled fragment shader when at least one graphics shader is attached.";
3319 return false;
3320 }
3321 ASSERT(fragmentShader->getType() == ShaderType::Fragment);
3322
3323 if (!vertexShader || !vertexShader->isCompiled())
3324 {
3325 infoLog
3326 << "No compiled vertex shader when at least one graphics shader is attached.";
3327 return false;
3328 }
3329 ASSERT(vertexShader->getType() == ShaderType::Vertex);
3330 }
3331
3332 if (vertexShader && fragmentShader)
3333 {
3334 int vertexShaderVersion = vertexShader->getShaderVersion();
3335 int fragmentShaderVersion = fragmentShader->getShaderVersion();
3336
3337 if (fragmentShaderVersion != vertexShaderVersion)
3338 {
3339 infoLog << "Fragment shader version does not match vertex shader version.";
3340 return false;
3341 }
3342 }
3343
3344 if (geometryShader)
3345 {
3346 // [GL_EXT_geometry_shader] Chapter 7
3347 // Linking can fail for a variety of reasons as specified in the OpenGL ES Shading
3348 // Language Specification, as well as any of the following reasons:
3349 // * One or more of the shader objects attached to <program> are not compiled
3350 // successfully.
3351 // * The shaders do not use the same shader language version.
3352 // * <program> contains objects to form a geometry shader, and
3353 // - <program> is not separable and contains no objects to form a vertex shader; or
3354 // - the input primitive type, output primitive type, or maximum output vertex count
3355 // is not specified in the compiled geometry shader object.
3356 if (!geometryShader->isCompiled())
3357 {
3358 infoLog << "The attached geometry shader isn't compiled.";
3359 return false;
3360 }
3361
3362 if (vertexShader &&
3363 (geometryShader->getShaderVersion() != vertexShader->getShaderVersion()))
3364 {
3365 infoLog << "Geometry shader version does not match vertex shader version.";
3366 return false;
3367 }
3368 ASSERT(geometryShader->getType() == ShaderType::Geometry);
3369
3370 Optional<PrimitiveMode> inputPrimitive =
3371 geometryShader->getGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType();
3372 if (!inputPrimitive.valid())
3373 {
3374 infoLog << "Input primitive type is not specified in the geometry shader.";
3375 return false;
3376 }
3377
3378 Optional<PrimitiveMode> outputPrimitive =
3379 geometryShader->getGeometryShaderOutputPrimitiveType();
3380 if (!outputPrimitive.valid())
3381 {
3382 infoLog << "Output primitive type is not specified in the geometry shader.";
3383 return false;
3384 }
3385
3386 Optional<GLint> maxVertices = geometryShader->getGeometryShaderMaxVertices();
3387 if (!maxVertices.valid())
3388 {
3389 infoLog << "'max_vertices' is not specified in the geometry shader.";
3390 return false;
3391 }
3392
3393 mState.mGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType = inputPrimitive.value();
3394 mState.mGeometryShaderOutputPrimitiveType = outputPrimitive.value();
3395 mState.mGeometryShaderMaxVertices = maxVertices.value();
3396 mState.mGeometryShaderInvocations = geometryShader->getGeometryShaderInvocations();
3397 }
3398 }
3399
3400 return true;
3401}

3474
3475bool Program::linkVaryings(InfoLog &infoLog) const
3476{
3477 ShaderType previousShaderType = ShaderType::InvalidEnum;
3478 for (ShaderType shaderType : kAllGraphicsShaderTypes)
3479 {
3480 Shader *currentShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType];
3481 if (!currentShader)
3482 {
3483 continue;
3484 }
3485
3486 if (previousShaderType != ShaderType::InvalidEnum)
3487 {
3488 Shader *previousShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[previousShaderType];
3489 const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &outputVaryings =
3490 previousShader->getOutputVaryings();
3491
3492 if (!linkValidateShaderInterfaceMatching(
3493 outputVaryings, currentShader->getInputVaryings(), previousShaderType,
3494 currentShader->getType(), previousShader->getShaderVersion(),
3495 currentShader->getShaderVersion(), isSeparable(), infoLog))
3496 {
3497 return false;
3498 }
3499 }
3500 previousShaderType = currentShader->getType();
3501 }
3502
3503 Shader *vertexShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Vertex];
3504 Shader *fragmentShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Fragment];
3505 if (vertexShader && fragmentShader &&
3506 !linkValidateBuiltInVaryings(vertexShader->getOutputVaryings(),
3507 fragmentShader->getInputVaryings(),
3508 vertexShader->getShaderVersion(), infoLog))
3509 {
3510 return false;
3511 }
3512
3513 return true;
3514}

3516void Program::getFilteredVaryings(const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &varyings,
3517 std::vector<const sh::ShaderVariable *> *filteredVaryingsOut)
3518{
3519 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : varyings)
3520 {
3521 // Built-in varyings obey special rules
3522 if (varying.isBuiltIn())
3523 {
3524 continue;
3525 }
3526

3530
3531bool Program::doShaderVariablesMatch(int outputShaderVersion,
3532 ShaderType outputShaderType,
3533 ShaderType inputShaderType,
3534 const sh::ShaderVariable &input,
3535 const sh::ShaderVariable &output,
3536 bool validateGeometryShaderInputs,
3537 bool isSeparable,
3538 gl::InfoLog &infoLog)
3539{
3540 bool namesMatch = input.name == output.name;
3541 bool locationsMatch = (input.location != -1) && (input.location == output.location);
3542
3543 // An output variable is considered to match an input variable in the subsequent
3544 // shader if:
3545 // - the two variables match in name, type, and qualification; or
3546 // - the two variables are declared with the same location qualifier and
3547 // match in type and qualification.
3548
3549 if (namesMatch || locationsMatch)
3550 {
3551 std::string mismatchedStructFieldName;
3552 LinkMismatchError linkError =
3553 LinkValidateVaryings(output, input, outputShaderVersion, validateGeometryShaderInputs,
3554 isSeparable, &mismatchedStructFieldName);
3555 if (linkError != LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH)
3556 {
3557 LogLinkMismatch(infoLog, input.name, "varying", linkError, mismatchedStructFieldName,
3558 outputShaderType, inputShaderType);
3559 return false;
3560 }
3561
3562 return true;
3563 }
3564
3565 return false;
3566}
3567
3568// [OpenGL ES 3.1] Chapter 7.4.1 "Shader Interface Matching" Page 91
3569// TODO(jiawei.shao@intel.com): add validation on input/output blocks matching
3570bool Program::linkValidateShaderInterfaceMatching(
3571 const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &outputVaryings,
3572 const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &inputVaryings,
3573 ShaderType outputShaderType,
3574 ShaderType inputShaderType,
3575 int outputShaderVersion,
3576 int inputShaderVersion,
3577 bool isSeparable,
3578 gl::InfoLog &infoLog)
3579{
3580 ASSERT(outputShaderVersion == inputShaderVersion);
3581
3582 std::vector<const sh::ShaderVariable *> filteredInputVaryings;
3583 std::vector<const sh::ShaderVariable *> filteredOutputVaryings;
3584 bool validateGeometryShaderInputs = inputShaderType == ShaderType::Geometry;
3585
3586 getFilteredVaryings(inputVaryings, &filteredInputVaryings);
3587 getFilteredVaryings(outputVaryings, &filteredOutputVaryings);
3588
3589 // Separable programs require the number of inputs and outputs match
3590 if (isSeparable && filteredInputVaryings.size() < filteredOutputVaryings.size())
3591 {
3592 infoLog << GetShaderTypeString(inputShaderType)
3593 << " does not consume all varyings generated by "
3594 << GetShaderTypeString(outputShaderType);
3595 return false;
3596 }
3597 if (isSeparable && filteredInputVaryings.size() > filteredOutputVaryings.size())
3598 {
3599 infoLog << GetShaderTypeString(outputShaderType)
3600 << " does not generate all varyings consumed by "
3601 << GetShaderTypeString(inputShaderType);
3602 return false;
3603 }
3604
3605 // All inputs must match all outputs
3606 for (const sh::ShaderVariable *input : filteredInputVaryings)
3607 {
3608 bool match = false;
3609 for (const sh::ShaderVariable *output : filteredOutputVaryings)
3610 {
3611 if (doShaderVariablesMatch(outputShaderVersion, outputShaderType, inputShaderType,
3612 *input, *output, validateGeometryShaderInputs, isSeparable,
3613 infoLog))
3614 {
3615 match = true;
3616 break;
3617 }
3618 }
3619
3620 // We permit unmatched, unreferenced varyings. Note that this specifically depends on
3621 // whether the input is statically used - a statically used input should fail this test even
3622 // if it is not active. GLSL ES 3.00.6 section 4.3.10.
3623 if (!match && input->staticUse)
3624 {
3625 infoLog << GetShaderTypeString(inputShaderType) << " varying " << input->name
3626 << " does not match any " << GetShaderTypeString(outputShaderType)
3627 << " varying";
3628 return false;
3629 }
3630 }
3631
3632 return true;
3633}

3670
3671void Program::linkSamplerAndImageBindings(GLuint *combinedImageUniforms)
3672{
3673 ASSERT(combinedImageUniforms);
3674
3675 // Iterate over mExecutable->mUniforms from the back, and find the range of atomic counters,
3676 // images and samplers in that order.
3677 auto highIter = mState.mExecutable->getUniforms().rbegin();
3678 auto lowIter = highIter;
3679
3680 unsigned int high = static_cast<unsigned int>(mState.mExecutable->getUniforms().size());
3681 unsigned int low = high;
3682
3683 // Note that uniform block uniforms are not yet appended to this list.
3684 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->getUniforms().size() == 0 || highIter->isAtomicCounter() ||
3685 highIter->isImage() || highIter->isSampler() || highIter->isInDefaultBlock());
3686
3687 for (; lowIter != mState.mExecutable->getUniforms().rend() && lowIter->isAtomicCounter();
3688 ++lowIter)
3689 {
3690 --low;
3691 }
3692
3693 mState.mAtomicCounterUniformRange = RangeUI(low, high);
3694
3695 highIter = lowIter;
3696 high = low;
3697
3698 for (; lowIter != mState.mExecutable->getUniforms().rend() && lowIter->isImage(); ++lowIter)
3699 {
3700 --low;
3701 }
3702
3703 mState.mExecutable->mImageUniformRange = RangeUI(low, high);
3704 *combinedImageUniforms = 0u;
3705 // The Program is still linking, so getExecutable().isCompute() isn't accurate yet.
3706 bool hasComputeShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Compute] != nullptr;
3707 std::vector<ImageBinding> &imageBindings = hasComputeShader
3708 ? mState.mExecutable->mComputeImageBindings
3709 : mState.mExecutable->mGraphicsImageBindings;
3710 // The arrays of arrays are flattened to arrays, it needs to record the array offset for the
3711 // correct binding image unit.
3712 uint32_t arrayOffset = 0;
3713 // If uniform is a image type, insert it into the mImageBindings array.
3714 for (unsigned int imageIndex : mState.mExecutable->getImageUniformRange())
3715 {
3716 // ES3.1 (section 7.6.1) and GLSL ES3.1 (section 4.4.5), Uniform*i{v} commands
3717 // cannot load values into a uniform defined as an image. if declare without a
3718 // binding qualifier, any uniform image variable (include all elements of
3719 // unbound image array) shoud be bound to unit zero.
3720 auto &imageUniform = mState.mExecutable->getUniforms()[imageIndex];
3721 if (imageUniform.binding == -1)
3722 {
3723 imageBindings.emplace_back(ImageBinding(imageUniform.getBasicTypeElementCount()));
3724 }
3725 else
3726 {
3727 imageBindings.emplace_back(ImageBinding(imageUniform.binding + arrayOffset,
3728 imageUniform.getBasicTypeElementCount()));
3729 }
3730
3731 GLuint arraySize = imageUniform.isArray() ? imageUniform.arraySizes[0] : 1u;
3732 *combinedImageUniforms += imageUniform.activeShaderCount() * arraySize;
3733 if (imageUniform.hasParentArrayIndex() && imageUniform.isArray())
3734 {
3735 arrayOffset += arraySize;
3736 }
3737 else
3738 {
3739 arrayOffset = 0;
3740 }
3741 }
3742
3743 highIter = lowIter;
3744 high = low;
3745
3746 for (; lowIter != mState.mExecutable->getUniforms().rend() && lowIter->isSampler(); ++lowIter)
3747 {
3748 --low;
3749 }
3750
3751 mState.mExecutable->mSamplerUniformRange = RangeUI(low, high);
3752
3753 // If uniform is a sampler type, insert it into the mSamplerBindings array.
3754 for (unsigned int samplerIndex : mState.mExecutable->getSamplerUniformRange())
3755 {
3756 const auto &samplerUniform = mState.mExecutable->getUniforms()[samplerIndex];
3757 TextureType textureType = SamplerTypeToTextureType(samplerUniform.type);
3758 unsigned int elementCount = samplerUniform.getBasicTypeElementCount();
3759 SamplerFormat format = samplerUniform.typeInfo->samplerFormat;
3760 mState.mExecutable->mSamplerBindings.emplace_back(textureType, format, elementCount);
3761 }
3762
3763 // Whatever is left constitutes the default uniforms.
3764 mState.mExecutable->mDefaultUniformRange = RangeUI(0, low);
3765}
3766
3767bool Program::linkAtomicCounterBuffers()
3768{
3769 for (unsigned int index : mState.mAtomicCounterUniformRange)
3770 {
3771 auto &uniform = mState.mExecutable->mUniforms[index];
3772 uniform.blockInfo.offset = uniform.offset;
3773 uniform.blockInfo.arrayStride = (uniform.isArray() ? 4 : 0);
3774 uniform.blockInfo.matrixStride = 0;
3775 uniform.blockInfo.isRowMajorMatrix = false;
3776
3777 bool found = false;
3778 for (unsigned int bufferIndex = 0;
3779 bufferIndex < mState.mExecutable->getActiveAtomicCounterBufferCount(); ++bufferIndex)
3780 {
3781 auto &buffer = mState.mExecutable->mAtomicCounterBuffers[bufferIndex];
3782 if (buffer.binding == uniform.binding)
3783 {
3784 buffer.memberIndexes.push_back(index);
3785 uniform.bufferIndex = bufferIndex;
3786 found = true;
3787 buffer.unionReferencesWith(uniform);
3788 break;
3789 }
3790 }
3791 if (!found)
3792 {
3793 AtomicCounterBuffer atomicCounterBuffer;
3794 atomicCounterBuffer.binding = uniform.binding;
3795 atomicCounterBuffer.memberIndexes.push_back(index);
3796 atomicCounterBuffer.unionReferencesWith(uniform);
3797 mState.mExecutable->mAtomicCounterBuffers.push_back(atomicCounterBuffer);
3798 uniform.bufferIndex =
3799 static_cast<int>(mState.mExecutable->getActiveAtomicCounterBufferCount() - 1);
3800 }
3801 }
3802 // TODO(jie.a.chen@intel.com): Count each atomic counter buffer to validate against
3803 // gl_Max[Vertex|Fragment|Compute|Geometry|Combined]AtomicCounterBuffers.
3804
3805 return true;
3806}
3807
3808// Assigns locations to all attributes (except built-ins) from the bindings and program locations.
3809bool Program::linkAttributes(const Context *context, InfoLog &infoLog)
3810{
3811 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
3812 const Limitations &limitations = context->getLimitations();
3813 bool webglCompatibility = context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility;
3814 int shaderVersion = -1;
3815 unsigned int usedLocations = 0;
3816
3817 Shader *vertexShader = mState.getAttachedShader(gl::ShaderType::Vertex);
3818
3819 if (!vertexShader)
3820 {
3821 // No vertex shader, so no attributes, so nothing to do
3822 return true;
3823 }
3824
3825 shaderVersion = vertexShader->getShaderVersion();
3826 if (shaderVersion >= 300)
3827 {
3828 // In GLSL ES 3.00.6, aliasing checks should be done with all declared attributes -
3829 // see GLSL ES 3.00.6 section 12.46. Inactive attributes will be pruned after
3830 // aliasing checks.
3831 mState.mExecutable->mProgramInputs = vertexShader->getAllAttributes();
3832 }
3833 else
3834 {
3835 // In GLSL ES 1.00.17 we only do aliasing checks for active attributes.
3836 mState.mExecutable->mProgramInputs = vertexShader->getActiveAttributes();
3837 }
3838
3839 GLuint maxAttribs = static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxVertexAttributes);
3840 std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable *> usedAttribMap(maxAttribs, nullptr);
3841
3842 // Assign locations to attributes that have a binding location and check for attribute aliasing.
3843 for (sh::ShaderVariable &attribute : mState.mExecutable->mProgramInputs)
3844 {
3845 // GLSL ES 3.10 January 2016 section 4.3.4: Vertex shader inputs can't be arrays or
3846 // structures, so we don't need to worry about adjusting their names or generating entries
3847 // for each member/element (unlike uniforms for example).
3848 ASSERT(!attribute.isArray() && !attribute.isStruct());
3849
3850 int bindingLocation = mAttributeBindings.getBinding(attribute);
3851 if (attribute.location == -1 && bindingLocation != -1)
3852 {
3853 attribute.location = bindingLocation;
3854 }
3855
3856 if (attribute.location != -1)
3857 {
3858 // Location is set by glBindAttribLocation or by location layout qualifier
3859 const int regs = VariableRegisterCount(attribute.type);
3860
3861 if (static_cast<GLuint>(regs + attribute.location) > maxAttribs)
3862 {
3863 infoLog << "Attribute (" << attribute.name << ") at location " << attribute.location
3864 << " is too big to fit";
3865
3866 return false;
3867 }
3868
3869 for (int reg = 0; reg < regs; reg++)
3870 {
3871 const int regLocation = attribute.location + reg;
3872 sh::ShaderVariable *linkedAttribute = usedAttribMap[regLocation];
3873
3874 // In GLSL ES 3.00.6 and in WebGL, attribute aliasing produces a link error.
3875 // In non-WebGL GLSL ES 1.00.17, attribute aliasing is allowed with some
3876 // restrictions - see GLSL ES 1.00.17 section 2.10.4, but ANGLE currently has a bug.
3877 // In D3D 9 and 11, aliasing is not supported, so check a limitation.
3878 if (linkedAttribute)
3879 {
3880 if (shaderVersion >= 300 || webglCompatibility ||
3881 limitations.noVertexAttributeAliasing)
3882 {
3883 infoLog << "Attribute '" << attribute.name << "' aliases attribute '"
3884 << linkedAttribute->name << "' at location " << regLocation;
3885 return false;
3886 }
3887 }
3888 else
3889 {
3890 usedAttribMap[regLocation] = &attribute;
3891 }
3892
3893 usedLocations |= 1 << regLocation;
3894 }
3895 }
3896 }
3897
3898 // Assign locations to attributes that don't have a binding location.
3899 for (sh::ShaderVariable &attribute : mState.mExecutable->mProgramInputs)
3900 {
3901 // Not set by glBindAttribLocation or by location layout qualifier
3902 if (attribute.location == -1)
3903 {
3904 int regs = VariableRegisterCount(attribute.type);
3905 int availableIndex = AllocateFirstFreeBits(&usedLocations, regs, maxAttribs);
3906
3907 if (availableIndex == -1 || static_cast<GLuint>(availableIndex + regs) > maxAttribs)
3908 {
3909 infoLog << "Too many attributes (" << attribute.name << ")";
3910 return false;
3911 }
3912
3913 attribute.location = availableIndex;
3914 }
3915 }
3916
3917 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->mAttributesTypeMask.none());
3918 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->mAttributesMask.none());
3919
3920 // Prune inactive attributes. This step is only needed on shaderVersion >= 300 since on earlier
3921 // shader versions we're only processing active attributes to begin with.
3922 if (shaderVersion >= 300)
3923 {
3924 for (auto attributeIter = mState.mExecutable->getProgramInputs().begin();
3925 attributeIter != mState.mExecutable->getProgramInputs().end();)
3926 {
3927 if (attributeIter->active)
3928 {
3929 ++attributeIter;
3930 }
3931 else
3932 {
3933 attributeIter = mState.mExecutable->mProgramInputs.erase(attributeIter);
3934 }
3935 }
3936 }
3937
3938 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &attribute : mState.mExecutable->getProgramInputs())
3939 {
3940 ASSERT(attribute.active);
3941 ASSERT(attribute.location != -1);
3942 unsigned int regs = static_cast<unsigned int>(VariableRegisterCount(attribute.type));
3943
3944 unsigned int location = static_cast<unsigned int>(attribute.location);
3945 for (unsigned int r = 0; r < regs; r++)
3946 {
3947 // Built-in active program inputs don't have a bound attribute.
3948 if (!attribute.isBuiltIn())
3949 {
3950 mState.mExecutable->mActiveAttribLocationsMask.set(location);
3951 mState.mExecutable->mMaxActiveAttribLocation =
3952 std::max(mState.mExecutable->mMaxActiveAttribLocation, location + 1);
3953
3954 ComponentType componentType =
3955 GLenumToComponentType(VariableComponentType(attribute.type));
3956
3957 SetComponentTypeMask(componentType, location,
3958 &mState.mExecutable->mAttributesTypeMask);
3959 mState.mExecutable->mAttributesMask.set(location);
3960
3961 location++;
3962 }
3963 }
3964 }
3965
3966 return true;
3967}
