3969bool Program::linkInterfaceBlocks(const Caps &caps,
3970 const Version &version,
3971 bool webglCompatibility,
3972 InfoLog &infoLog,
3973 GLuint *combinedShaderStorageBlocksCount)
3974{
3975 ASSERT(combinedShaderStorageBlocksCount);
3976
3977 GLuint combinedUniformBlocksCount = 0u;
3978 GLuint numShadersHasUniformBlocks = 0u;
3979 ShaderMap<const std::vector<sh::InterfaceBlock> *> allShaderUniformBlocks = {};
3980 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
3981 {
3982 Shader *shader = mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType];
3983 if (!shader)
3984 {
3985 continue;
3986 }
3987
3988 const auto &uniformBlocks = shader->getUniformBlocks();
3989 if (!uniformBlocks.empty())
3990 {
3991 if (!ValidateInterfaceBlocksCount(
3992 static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxShaderUniformBlocks[shaderType]), uniformBlocks,
3993 shaderType, sh::BlockType::BLOCK_UNIFORM, &combinedUniformBlocksCount, infoLog))
3994 {
3995 return false;
3996 }
3997
3998 allShaderUniformBlocks[shaderType] = &uniformBlocks;
3999 ++numShadersHasUniformBlocks;
4000 }
4001 }
4002
4003 if (combinedUniformBlocksCount > static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxCombinedUniformBlocks))
4004 {
4005 infoLog << "The sum of the number of active uniform blocks exceeds "
4006 "MAX_COMBINED_UNIFORM_BLOCKS ("
4007 << caps.maxCombinedUniformBlocks << ").";
4008 return false;
4009 }
4010
4011 if (!ValidateInterfaceBlocksMatch(numShadersHasUniformBlocks, allShaderUniformBlocks, infoLog,
4012 webglCompatibility))
4013 {
4014 return false;
4015 }
4016
4017 if (version >= Version(3, 1))
4018 {
4019 *combinedShaderStorageBlocksCount = 0u;
4020 GLuint numShadersHasShaderStorageBlocks = 0u;
4021 ShaderMap<const std::vector<sh::InterfaceBlock> *> allShaderStorageBlocks = {};
4022 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
4023 {
4024 Shader *shader = mState.mAttachedShaders[shaderType];
4025 if (!shader)
4026 {
4027 continue;
4028 }
4029
4030 const auto &shaderStorageBlocks = shader->getShaderStorageBlocks();
4031 if (!shaderStorageBlocks.empty())
4032 {
4033 if (!ValidateInterfaceBlocksCount(
4034 static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxShaderStorageBlocks[shaderType]),
4035 shaderStorageBlocks, shaderType, sh::BlockType::BLOCK_BUFFER,
4036 combinedShaderStorageBlocksCount, infoLog))
4037 {
4038 return false;
4039 }
4040
4041 allShaderStorageBlocks[shaderType] = &shaderStorageBlocks;
4042 ++numShadersHasShaderStorageBlocks;
4043 }
4044 }
4045
4046 if (*combinedShaderStorageBlocksCount >
4047 static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxCombinedShaderStorageBlocks))
4048 {
4049 infoLog << "The sum of the number of active shader storage blocks exceeds "
4050 "MAX_COMBINED_SHADER_STORAGE_BLOCKS ("
4051 << caps.maxCombinedShaderStorageBlocks << ").";
4052 return false;
4053 }
4054
4055 if (!ValidateInterfaceBlocksMatch(numShadersHasShaderStorageBlocks, allShaderStorageBlocks,
4056 infoLog, webglCompatibility))
4057 {
4058 return false;
4059 }
4060 }
4061
4062 return true;
4063}
4064
4065LinkMismatchError Program::LinkValidateVariablesBase(const sh::ShaderVariable &variable1,
4066 const sh::ShaderVariable &variable2,
4067 bool validatePrecision,
4068 bool validateArraySize,
4069 std::string *mismatchedStructOrBlockMemberName)
4070{
4071 if (variable1.type != variable2.type)
4072 {
4073 return LinkMismatchError::TYPE_MISMATCH;
4074 }
4075 if (validateArraySize && variable1.arraySizes != variable2.arraySizes)
4076 {
4077 return LinkMismatchError::ARRAY_SIZE_MISMATCH;
4078 }
4079 if (validatePrecision && variable1.precision != variable2.precision)
4080 {
4081 return LinkMismatchError::PRECISION_MISMATCH;
4082 }
4083 if (variable1.structName != variable2.structName)
4084 {
4085 return LinkMismatchError::STRUCT_NAME_MISMATCH;
4086 }
4087 if (variable1.imageUnitFormat != variable2.imageUnitFormat)
4088 {
4089 return LinkMismatchError::FORMAT_MISMATCH;
4090 }
4091
4092 if (variable1.fields.size() != variable2.fields.size())
4093 {
4094 return LinkMismatchError::FIELD_NUMBER_MISMATCH;
4095 }
4096 const unsigned int numMembers = static_cast<unsigned int>(variable1.fields.size());
4097 for (unsigned int memberIndex = 0; memberIndex < numMembers; memberIndex++)
4098 {
4099 const sh::ShaderVariable &member1 = variable1.fields[memberIndex];
4100 const sh::ShaderVariable &member2 = variable2.fields[memberIndex];
4101
4102 if (member1.name != member2.name)
4103 {
4104 return LinkMismatchError::FIELD_NAME_MISMATCH;
4105 }
4106
4107 LinkMismatchError linkErrorOnField = LinkValidateVariablesBase(
4108 member1, member2, validatePrecision, true, mismatchedStructOrBlockMemberName);
4109 if (linkErrorOnField != LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH)
4110 {
4111 AddParentPrefix(member1.name, mismatchedStructOrBlockMemberName);
4112 return linkErrorOnField;
4113 }
4114 }
4115
4116 return LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH;
4117}
4118
4119LinkMismatchError Program::LinkValidateVaryings(const sh::ShaderVariable &outputVarying,
4120 const sh::ShaderVariable &inputVarying,
4121 int shaderVersion,
4122 bool validateGeometryShaderInputVarying,
4123 bool isSeparable,
4124 std::string *mismatchedStructFieldName)
4125{
4126 if (validateGeometryShaderInputVarying)
4127 {
4128 // [GL_EXT_geometry_shader] Section 11.1gs.4.3:
4129 // The OpenGL ES Shading Language doesn't support multi-dimensional arrays as shader inputs
4130 // or outputs.
4131 ASSERT(inputVarying.arraySizes.size() == 1u);
4132
4133 // Geometry shader input varyings are not treated as arrays, so a vertex array output
4134 // varying cannot match a geometry shader input varying.
4135 // [GL_EXT_geometry_shader] Section 7.4.1:
4136 // Geometry shader per-vertex input variables and blocks are required to be declared as
4137 // arrays, with each element representing input or output values for a single vertex of a
4138 // multi-vertex primitive. For the purposes of interface matching, such variables and blocks
4139 // are treated as though they were not declared as arrays.
4140 if (outputVarying.isArray())
4141 {
4142 return LinkMismatchError::ARRAY_SIZE_MISMATCH;
4143 }
4144 }
4145
4146 // Skip the validation on the array sizes between a vertex output varying and a geometry input
4147 // varying as it has been done before.
4148 bool validatePrecision = isSeparable && (shaderVersion > 100);
4149 LinkMismatchError linkError =
4150 LinkValidateVariablesBase(outputVarying, inputVarying, validatePrecision,
4151 !validateGeometryShaderInputVarying, mismatchedStructFieldName);
4152 if (linkError != LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH)
4153 {
4154 return linkError;
4155 }
4156
4157 // Explicit locations must match if the names match.
4158 if ((outputVarying.name == inputVarying.name) &&
4159 (outputVarying.location != inputVarying.location))
4160 {
4161 return LinkMismatchError::LOCATION_MISMATCH;
4162 }
4163
4164 if (!sh::InterpolationTypesMatch(outputVarying.interpolation, inputVarying.interpolation))
4165 {
4166 return LinkMismatchError::INTERPOLATION_TYPE_MISMATCH;
4167 }
4168
4169 if (shaderVersion == 100 && outputVarying.isInvariant != inputVarying.isInvariant)
4170 {
4171 return LinkMismatchError::INVARIANCE_MISMATCH;
4172 }
4173
4174 return LinkMismatchError::NO_MISMATCH;
4175}
4176
4177bool Program::linkValidateBuiltInVaryings(const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &vertexVaryings,
4178 const std::vector<sh::ShaderVariable> &fragmentVaryings,
4179 int vertexShaderVersion,
4180 InfoLog &infoLog)
4181{
4182 if (vertexShaderVersion != 100)
4183 {
4184 // Only ESSL 1.0 has restrictions on matching input and output invariance
4185 return true;
4186 }
4187
4188 bool glPositionIsInvariant = false;
4189 bool glPointSizeIsInvariant = false;
4190 bool glFragCoordIsInvariant = false;
4191 bool glPointCoordIsInvariant = false;
4192
4193 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : vertexVaryings)
4194 {
4195 if (!varying.isBuiltIn())
4196 {
4197 continue;
4198 }
4199 if (varying.name.compare("gl_Position") == 0)
4200 {
4201 glPositionIsInvariant = varying.isInvariant;
4202 }
4203 else if (varying.name.compare("gl_PointSize") == 0)
4204 {
4205 glPointSizeIsInvariant = varying.isInvariant;
4206 }
4207 }
4208
4209 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : fragmentVaryings)
4210 {
4211 if (!varying.isBuiltIn())
4212 {
4213 continue;
4214 }
4215 if (varying.name.compare("gl_FragCoord") == 0)
4216 {
4217 glFragCoordIsInvariant = varying.isInvariant;
4218 }
4219 else if (varying.name.compare("gl_PointCoord") == 0)
4220 {
4221 glPointCoordIsInvariant = varying.isInvariant;
4222 }
4223 }
4224
4225 // There is some ambiguity in ESSL 1.00.17 paragraph 4.6.4 interpretation,
4226 // for example, https://cvs.khronos.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=13842.
4227 // Not requiring invariance to match is supported by:
4228 // dEQP, WebGL CTS, Nexus 5X GLES
4229 if (glFragCoordIsInvariant && !glPositionIsInvariant)
4230 {
4231 infoLog << "gl_FragCoord can only be declared invariant if and only if gl_Position is "
4232 "declared invariant.";
4233 return false;
4234 }
4235 if (glPointCoordIsInvariant && !glPointSizeIsInvariant)
4236 {
4237 infoLog << "gl_PointCoord can only be declared invariant if and only if gl_PointSize is "
4238 "declared invariant.";
4239 return false;
4240 }
4241
4242 return true;
4243}
4244
4245bool Program::linkValidateTransformFeedback(const Version &version,
4246 InfoLog &infoLog,
4247 const ProgramMergedVaryings &varyings,
4248 ShaderType stage,
4249 const Caps &caps) const
4250{
4251
4252 // Validate the tf names regardless of the actual program varyings.
4253 std::set<std::string> uniqueNames;
4254 for (const std::string &tfVaryingName : mState.mTransformFeedbackVaryingNames)
4255 {
4256 if (version < Version(3, 1) && tfVaryingName.find('[') != std::string::npos)
4257 {
4258 infoLog << "Capture of array elements is undefined and not supported.";
4259 return false;
4260 }
4261 if (version >= Version(3, 1))
4262 {
4263 if (IncludeSameArrayElement(uniqueNames, tfVaryingName))
4264 {
4265 infoLog << "Two transform feedback varyings include the same array element ("
4266 << tfVaryingName << ").";
4267 return false;
4268 }
4269 }
4270 else
4271 {
4272 if (uniqueNames.count(tfVaryingName) > 0)
4273 {
4274 infoLog << "Two transform feedback varyings specify the same output variable ("
4275 << tfVaryingName << ").";
4276 return false;
4277 }
4278 }
4279 uniqueNames.insert(tfVaryingName);
4280 }
4281
4282 // Validate against program varyings.
4283 size_t totalComponents = 0;
4284 for (const std::string &tfVaryingName : mState.mTransformFeedbackVaryingNames)
4285 {
4286 std::vector<unsigned int> subscripts;
4287 std::string baseName = ParseResourceName(tfVaryingName, &subscripts);
4288
4289 const sh::ShaderVariable *var = FindOutputVaryingOrField(varyings, stage, baseName);
4290 if (var == nullptr)
4291 {
4292 infoLog << "Transform feedback varying " << tfVaryingName
4293 << " does not exist in the vertex shader.";
4294 return false;
4295 }
4296
4297 // Validate the matching variable.
4298 if (var->isStruct())
4299 {
4300 infoLog << "Struct cannot be captured directly (" << baseName << ").";
4301 return false;
4302 }
4303
4304 size_t elementCount = 0;
4305 size_t componentCount = 0;
4306
4307 if (var->isArray())
4308 {
4309 if (version < Version(3, 1))
4310 {
4311 infoLog << "Capture of arrays is undefined and not supported.";
4312 return false;
4313 }
4314
4315 // GLSL ES 3.10 section 4.3.6: A vertex output can't be an array of arrays.
4316 ASSERT(!var->isArrayOfArrays());
4317
4318 if (!subscripts.empty() && subscripts[0] >= var->getOutermostArraySize())
4319 {
4320 infoLog << "Cannot capture outbound array element '" << tfVaryingName << "'.";
4321 return false;
4322 }
4323 elementCount = (subscripts.empty() ? var->getOutermostArraySize() : 1);
4324 }
4325 else
4326 {
4327 if (!subscripts.empty())
4328 {
4329 infoLog << "Varying '" << baseName
4330 << "' is not an array to be captured by element.";
4331 return false;
4332 }
4333 elementCount = 1;
4334 }
4335
4336 // TODO(jmadill): Investigate implementation limits on D3D11
4337 componentCount = VariableComponentCount(var->type) * elementCount;
4338 if (mState.mExecutable->getTransformFeedbackBufferMode() == GL_SEPARATE_ATTRIBS &&
4339 componentCount > static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxTransformFeedbackSeparateComponents))
4340 {
4341 infoLog << "Transform feedback varying " << tfVaryingName << " components ("
4342 << componentCount << ") exceed the maximum separate components ("
4343 << caps.maxTransformFeedbackSeparateComponents << ").";
4344 return false;
4345 }
4346
4347 totalComponents += componentCount;
4348 if (mState.mExecutable->getTransformFeedbackBufferMode() == GL_INTERLEAVED_ATTRIBS &&
4349 totalComponents > static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxTransformFeedbackInterleavedComponents))
4350 {
4351 infoLog << "Transform feedback varying total components (" << totalComponents
4352 << ") exceed the maximum interleaved components ("
4353 << caps.maxTransformFeedbackInterleavedComponents << ").";
4354 return false;
4355 }
4356 }
4357 return true;
4358}
4359
4360void Program::gatherTransformFeedbackVaryings(const ProgramMergedVaryings &varyings,
4361 ShaderType stage)
4362{
4363 // Gather the linked varyings that are used for transform feedback, they should all exist.
4364 mState.mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings.clear();
4365 for (const std::string &tfVaryingName : mState.mTransformFeedbackVaryingNames)
4366 {
4367 std::vector<unsigned int> subscripts;
4368 std::string baseName = ParseResourceName(tfVaryingName, &subscripts);
4369 size_t subscript = GL_INVALID_INDEX;
4370 if (!subscripts.empty())
4371 {
4372 subscript = subscripts.back();
4373 }
4374 for (const ProgramVaryingRef &ref : varyings)
4375 {
4376 if (ref.frontShaderStage != stage)
4377 {
4378 continue;
4379 }
4380
4381 const sh::ShaderVariable *varying = ref.get(stage);
4382 if (baseName == varying->name)
4383 {
4384 mState.mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings.emplace_back(
4385 *varying, static_cast<GLuint>(subscript));
4386 break;
4387 }
4388 else if (varying->isStruct())
4389 {
4390 GLuint fieldIndex = 0;
4391 const auto *field = varying->findField(tfVaryingName, &fieldIndex);
4392 if (field != nullptr)
4393 {
4394 mState.mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings.emplace_back(*field,
4395 *varying);
4396 break;
4397 }
4398 }
4399 }
4400 }
4401}
4402
4403ProgramMergedVaryings Program::getMergedVaryings() const
4404{
4405 ASSERT(mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Compute] == nullptr);
4406
4407 // Varyings are matched between pairs of consecutive stages, by location if assigned or
4408 // by name otherwise. Note that it's possible for one stage to specify location and the other
4409 // not: https://cvs.khronos.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=16261
4410
4411 // Map stages to the previous active stage in the rendering pipeline. When looking at input
4412 // varyings of a stage, this is used to find the stage whose output varyings are being linked
4413 // with them.
4414 ShaderMap<ShaderType> previousActiveStage;
4415
4416 // Note that kAllGraphicsShaderTypes is sorted according to the rendering pipeline.
4417 ShaderType lastActiveStage = ShaderType::InvalidEnum;
4418 for (ShaderType stage : kAllGraphicsShaderTypes)
4419 {
4420 previousActiveStage[stage] = lastActiveStage;
4421 if (mState.mAttachedShaders[stage])
4422 {
4423 lastActiveStage = stage;
4424 }
4425 }
4426
4427 // First, go through output varyings and create two maps (one by name, one by location) for
4428 // faster lookup when matching input varyings.
4429
4430 ShaderMap<std::map<std::string, size_t>> outputVaryingNameToIndex;
4431 ShaderMap<std::map<int, size_t>> outputVaryingLocationToIndex;
4432
4433 ProgramMergedVaryings merged;
4434
4435 // Gather output varyings.
4436 for (Shader *shader : mState.mAttachedShaders)
4437 {
4438 if (!shader)
4439 {
4440 continue;
4441 }
4442 ShaderType stage = shader->getType();
4443
4444 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : shader->getOutputVaryings())
4445 {
4446 merged.push_back({});
4447 ProgramVaryingRef *ref = &merged.back();
4448
4449 ref->frontShader = &varying;
4450 ref->frontShaderStage = stage;
4451
4452 // Always map by name. Even if location is provided in this stage, it may not be in the
4453 // paired stage.
4454 outputVaryingNameToIndex[stage][varying.name] = merged.size() - 1;
4455
4456 // If location is provided, also keep it in a map by location.
4457 if (varying.location != -1)
4458 {
4459 outputVaryingLocationToIndex[stage][varying.location] = merged.size() - 1;
4460 }
4461 }
4462 }
4463
4464 // Gather input varyings, and match them with output varyings of the previous stage.
4465 for (Shader *shader : mState.mAttachedShaders)
4466 {
4467 if (!shader)
4468 {
4469 continue;
4470 }
4471 ShaderType stage = shader->getType();
4472 ShaderType previousStage = previousActiveStage[stage];
4473
4474 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : shader->getInputVaryings())
4475 {
4476 size_t mergedIndex = merged.size();
4477 if (previousStage != ShaderType::InvalidEnum)
4478 {
4479 // If location is provided, see if we can match by location.
4480 if (varying.location != -1)
4481 {
4482 auto byLocationIter =
4483 outputVaryingLocationToIndex[previousStage].find(varying.location);
4484 if (byLocationIter != outputVaryingLocationToIndex[previousStage].end())
4485 {
4486 mergedIndex = byLocationIter->second;
4487 }
4488 }
4489
4490 // If not found, try to match by name.
4491 if (mergedIndex == merged.size())
4492 {
4493 auto byNameIter = outputVaryingNameToIndex[previousStage].find(varying.name);
4494 if (byNameIter != outputVaryingNameToIndex[previousStage].end())
4495 {
4496 mergedIndex = byNameIter->second;
4497 }
4498 }
4499 }
4500
4501 // If no previous stage, or not matched by location or name, create a new entry for it.
4502 if (mergedIndex == merged.size())
4503 {
4504 merged.push_back({});
4505 mergedIndex = merged.size() - 1;
4506 }
4507
4508 ProgramVaryingRef *ref = &merged[mergedIndex];
4509
4510 ref->backShader = &varying;
4511 ref->backShaderStage = stage;
4512 }
4513 }
4514
4515 return merged;
4516}
4517
4518bool CompareOutputVariable(const sh::ShaderVariable &a, const sh::ShaderVariable &b)
4519{
4520 return a.getArraySizeProduct() > b.getArraySizeProduct();
4521}
4522
4523int Program::getOutputLocationForLink(const sh::ShaderVariable &outputVariable) const
4524{
4525 if (outputVariable.location != -1)
4526 {
4527 return outputVariable.location;
4528 }
4529 int apiLocation = mFragmentOutputLocations.getBinding(outputVariable);
4530 if (apiLocation != -1)
4531 {
4532 return apiLocation;
4533 }
4534 return -1;
4535}
4536
4537bool Program::isOutputSecondaryForLink(const sh::ShaderVariable &outputVariable) const
4538{
4539 if (outputVariable.index != -1)
4540 {
4541 ASSERT(outputVariable.index == 0 || outputVariable.index == 1);
4542 return (outputVariable.index == 1);
4543 }
4544 int apiIndex = mFragmentOutputIndexes.getBinding(outputVariable);
4545 if (apiIndex != -1)
4546 {
4547 // Index layout qualifier from the shader takes precedence, so the index from the API is
4548 // checked only if the index was not set in the shader. This is not specified in the EXT
4549 // spec, but is specified in desktop OpenGL specs.
4550 return (apiIndex == 1);
4551 }
4552 // EXT_blend_func_extended: Outputs get index 0 by default.
4553 return false;
4554}

4559bool FindUsedOutputLocation(std::vector<VariableLocation> &outputLocations,
4560 unsigned int baseLocation,
4561 unsigned int elementCount,
4562 const std::vector<VariableLocation> &reservedLocations,
4563 unsigned int variableIndex)
4564{
4565 if (baseLocation + elementCount > outputLocations.size())
4566 {
4567 elementCount = baseLocation < outputLocations.size()
4568 ? static_cast<unsigned int>(outputLocations.size() - baseLocation)
4569 : 0;
4570 }
4571 for (unsigned int elementIndex = 0; elementIndex < elementCount; elementIndex++)
4572 {
4573 const unsigned int location = baseLocation + elementIndex;
4574 if (outputLocations[location].used())
4575 {
4576 VariableLocation locationInfo(elementIndex, variableIndex);
4577 if (std::find(reservedLocations.begin(), reservedLocations.end(), locationInfo) ==
4578 reservedLocations.end())
4579 {
4580 return true;
4581 }
4582 }
4583 }
4584 return false;
4585}
4586
4587void AssignOutputLocations(std::vector<VariableLocation> &outputLocations,
4588 unsigned int baseLocation,
4589 unsigned int elementCount,
4590 const std::vector<VariableLocation> &reservedLocations,
4591 unsigned int variableIndex,
4592 sh::ShaderVariable &outputVariable)
4593{
4594 if (baseLocation + elementCount > outputLocations.size())
4595 {
4596 outputLocations.resize(baseLocation + elementCount);
4597 }
4598 for (unsigned int elementIndex = 0; elementIndex < elementCount; elementIndex++)
4599 {
4600 VariableLocation locationInfo(elementIndex, variableIndex);
4601 if (std::find(reservedLocations.begin(), reservedLocations.end(), locationInfo) ==
4602 reservedLocations.end())
4603 {
4604 outputVariable.location = baseLocation;
4605 const unsigned int location = baseLocation + elementIndex;
4606 outputLocations[location] = locationInfo;
4607 }
4608 }
4609}

4612
4613bool Program::linkOutputVariables(const Caps &caps,
4614 const Extensions &extensions,
4615 const Version &version,
4616 GLuint combinedImageUniformsCount,
4617 GLuint combinedShaderStorageBlocksCount)
4618{
4619 InfoLog &infoLog = mState.mExecutable->getInfoLog();
4620 Shader *fragmentShader = mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Fragment];
4621
4622 ASSERT(mState.mOutputVariableTypes.empty());
4623 ASSERT(mState.mActiveOutputVariables.none());
4624 ASSERT(mState.mDrawBufferTypeMask.none());
4625
4626 if (!fragmentShader)
4627 {
4628 // No fragment shader, so nothing to link
4629 return true;
4630 }
4631
4632 const auto &outputVariables = fragmentShader->getActiveOutputVariables();
4633
4634 // Gather output variable types
4635 for (const auto &outputVariable : outputVariables)
4636 {
4637 if (outputVariable.isBuiltIn() && outputVariable.name != "gl_FragColor" &&
4638 outputVariable.name != "gl_FragData")
4639 {
4640 continue;
4641 }
4642
4643 unsigned int baseLocation =
4644 (outputVariable.location == -1 ? 0u
4645 : static_cast<unsigned int>(outputVariable.location));
4646
4647 // GLSL ES 3.10 section 4.3.6: Output variables cannot be arrays of arrays or arrays of
4648 // structures, so we may use getBasicTypeElementCount().
4649 unsigned int elementCount = outputVariable.getBasicTypeElementCount();
4650 for (unsigned int elementIndex = 0; elementIndex < elementCount; elementIndex++)
4651 {
4652 const unsigned int location = baseLocation + elementIndex;
4653 if (location >= mState.mOutputVariableTypes.size())
4654 {
4655 mState.mOutputVariableTypes.resize(location + 1, GL_NONE);
4656 }
4657 ASSERT(location < mState.mActiveOutputVariables.size());
4658 mState.mActiveOutputVariables.set(location);
4659 mState.mOutputVariableTypes[location] = VariableComponentType(outputVariable.type);
4660 ComponentType componentType =
4661 GLenumToComponentType(mState.mOutputVariableTypes[location]);
4662 SetComponentTypeMask(componentType, location, &mState.mDrawBufferTypeMask);
4663 }
4664 }
4665
4666 if (version >= ES_3_1)
4667 {
4668 // [OpenGL ES 3.1] Chapter 8.22 Page 203:
4669 // A link error will be generated if the sum of the number of active image uniforms used in
4670 // all shaders, the number of active shader storage blocks, and the number of active
4671 // fragment shader outputs exceeds the implementation-dependent value of
4672 // MAX_COMBINED_SHADER_OUTPUT_RESOURCES.
4673 if (combinedImageUniformsCount + combinedShaderStorageBlocksCount +
4674 mState.mActiveOutputVariables.count() >
4675 static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxCombinedShaderOutputResources))
4676 {
4677 infoLog
4678 << "The sum of the number of active image uniforms, active shader storage blocks "
4679 "and active fragment shader outputs exceeds "
4680 "MAX_COMBINED_SHADER_OUTPUT_RESOURCES ("
4681 << caps.maxCombinedShaderOutputResources << ")";
4682 return false;
4683 }
4684 }
4685
4686 // Skip this step for GLES2 shaders.
4687 if (fragmentShader && fragmentShader->getShaderVersion() == 100)
4688 return true;
4689
4690 mState.mExecutable->mOutputVariables = outputVariables;
4691 // TODO(jmadill): any caps validation here?
4692
4693 // EXT_blend_func_extended doesn't specify anything related to binding specific elements of an
4694 // output array in explicit terms.
4695 //
4696 // Assuming fragData is an output array, you can defend the position that:
4697 // P1) you must support binding "fragData" because it's specified
4698 // P2) you must support querying "fragData[x]" because it's specified
4699 // P3) you must support binding "fragData[0]" because it's a frequently used pattern
4700 //
4701 // Then you can make the leap of faith:
4702 // P4) you must support binding "fragData[x]" because you support "fragData[0]"
4703 // P5) you must support binding "fragData[x]" because you support querying "fragData[x]"
4704 //
4705 // The spec brings in the "world of arrays" when it mentions binding the arrays and the
4706 // automatic binding. Thus it must be interpreted that the thing is not undefined, rather you
4707 // must infer the only possible interpretation (?). Note again: this need of interpretation
4708 // might be completely off of what GL spec logic is.
4709 //
4710 // The other complexity is that unless you implement this feature, it's hard to understand what
4711 // should happen when the client invokes the feature. You cannot add an additional error as it
4712 // is not specified. One can ignore it, but obviously it creates the discrepancies...
4713
4714 std::vector<VariableLocation> reservedLocations;
4715
4716 // Process any output API bindings for arrays that don't alias to the first element.
4717 for (const auto &binding : mFragmentOutputLocations)
4718 {
4719 size_t nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex;
4720 unsigned int arrayIndex = ParseArrayIndex(binding.first, &nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex);
4721 if (arrayIndex == 0 || arrayIndex == GL_INVALID_INDEX)
4722 {
4723 continue;
4724 }
4725 for (unsigned int outputVariableIndex = 0;
4726 outputVariableIndex < mState.mExecutable->getOutputVariables().size();
4727 outputVariableIndex++)
4728 {
4729 const sh::ShaderVariable &outputVariable =
4730 mState.mExecutable->getOutputVariables()[outputVariableIndex];
4731 // Check that the binding corresponds to an output array and its array index fits.
4732 if (outputVariable.isBuiltIn() || !outputVariable.isArray() ||
4733 !angle::BeginsWith(outputVariable.name, binding.first,
4734 nameLengthWithoutArrayIndex) ||
4735 arrayIndex >= outputVariable.getOutermostArraySize())
4736 {
4737 continue;
4738 }
4739
4740 // Get the API index that corresponds to this exact binding.
4741 // This index may differ from the index used for the array's base.
4742 auto &outputLocations = mFragmentOutputIndexes.getBindingByName(binding.first) == 1
4743 ? mState.mSecondaryOutputLocations
4744 : mState.mExecutable->mOutputLocations;
4745 unsigned int location = binding.second.location;
4746 VariableLocation locationInfo(arrayIndex, outputVariableIndex);
4747 if (location >= outputLocations.size())
4748 {
4749 outputLocations.resize(location + 1);
4750 }
4751 if (outputLocations[location].used())
4752 {
4753 infoLog << "Location of variable " << outputVariable.name
4754 << " conflicts with another variable.";
4755 return false;
4756 }
4757 outputLocations[location] = locationInfo;
4758
4759 // Note the array binding location so that it can be skipped later.
4760 reservedLocations.push_back(locationInfo);
4761 }
4762 }
4763
4764 // Reserve locations for output variables whose location is fixed in the shader or through the
4765 // API. Otherwise, the remaining unallocated outputs will be processed later.
4766 for (unsigned int outputVariableIndex = 0;
4767 outputVariableIndex < mState.mExecutable->getOutputVariables().size();
4768 outputVariableIndex++)
4769 {
4770 const sh::ShaderVariable &outputVariable =
4771 mState.mExecutable->getOutputVariables()[outputVariableIndex];
4772
4773 // Don't store outputs for gl_FragDepth, gl_FragColor, etc.
4774 if (outputVariable.isBuiltIn())
4775 continue;
4776
4777 int fixedLocation = getOutputLocationForLink(outputVariable);
4778 if (fixedLocation == -1)
4779 {
4780 // Here we're only reserving locations for variables whose location is fixed.
4781 continue;
4782 }
4783 unsigned int baseLocation = static_cast<unsigned int>(fixedLocation);
4784
4785 auto &outputLocations = isOutputSecondaryForLink(outputVariable)
4786 ? mState.mSecondaryOutputLocations
4787 : mState.mExecutable->mOutputLocations;
4788
4789 // GLSL ES 3.10 section 4.3.6: Output variables cannot be arrays of arrays or arrays of
4790 // structures, so we may use getBasicTypeElementCount().
4791 unsigned int elementCount = outputVariable.getBasicTypeElementCount();
4792 if (FindUsedOutputLocation(outputLocations, baseLocation, elementCount, reservedLocations,
4793 outputVariableIndex))
4794 {
4795 infoLog << "Location of variable " << outputVariable.name
4796 << " conflicts with another variable.";
4797 return false;
4798 }
4799 AssignOutputLocations(outputLocations, baseLocation, elementCount, reservedLocations,
4800 outputVariableIndex,
4801 mState.mExecutable->mOutputVariables[outputVariableIndex]);
4802 }
4803
4804 // Here we assign locations for the output variables that don't yet have them. Note that we're
4805 // not necessarily able to fit the variables optimally, since then we might have to try
4806 // different arrangements of output arrays. Now we just assign the locations in the order that
4807 // we got the output variables. The spec isn't clear on what kind of algorithm is required for
4808 // finding locations for the output variables, so this should be acceptable at least for now.
4809 GLuint maxLocation = static_cast<GLuint>(caps.maxDrawBuffers);
4810 if (!mState.mSecondaryOutputLocations.empty())
4811 {
4812 // EXT_blend_func_extended: Program outputs will be validated against
4813 // MAX_DUAL_SOURCE_DRAW_BUFFERS_EXT if there's even one output with index one.
4814 maxLocation = extensions.maxDualSourceDrawBuffers;
4815 }
4816
4817 for (unsigned int outputVariableIndex = 0;
4818 outputVariableIndex < mState.mExecutable->getOutputVariables().size();
4819 outputVariableIndex++)
4820 {
4821 const sh::ShaderVariable &outputVariable =
4822 mState.mExecutable->getOutputVariables()[outputVariableIndex];
4823
4824 // Don't store outputs for gl_FragDepth, gl_FragColor, etc.
4825 if (outputVariable.isBuiltIn())
4826 continue;
4827
4828 int fixedLocation = getOutputLocationForLink(outputVariable);
4829 auto &outputLocations = isOutputSecondaryForLink(outputVariable)
4830 ? mState.mSecondaryOutputLocations
4831 : mState.mExecutable->mOutputLocations;
4832 unsigned int baseLocation = 0;
4833 unsigned int elementCount = outputVariable.getBasicTypeElementCount();
4834 if (fixedLocation != -1)
4835 {
4836 // Secondary inputs might have caused the max location to drop below what has already
4837 // been explicitly assigned locations. Check for any fixed locations above the max
4838 // that should cause linking to fail.
4839 baseLocation = static_cast<unsigned int>(fixedLocation);
4840 }
4841 else
4842 {
4843 // No fixed location, so try to fit the output in unassigned locations.
4844 // Try baseLocations starting from 0 one at a time and see if the variable fits.
4845 while (FindUsedOutputLocation(outputLocations, baseLocation, elementCount,
4846 reservedLocations, outputVariableIndex))
4847 {
4848 baseLocation++;
4849 }
4850 AssignOutputLocations(outputLocations, baseLocation, elementCount, reservedLocations,
4851 outputVariableIndex,
4852 mState.mExecutable->mOutputVariables[outputVariableIndex]);
4853 }
4854
4855 // Check for any elements assigned above the max location that are actually used.
4856 if (baseLocation + elementCount > maxLocation &&
4857 (baseLocation >= maxLocation ||
4858 FindUsedOutputLocation(outputLocations, maxLocation,
4859 baseLocation + elementCount - maxLocation, reservedLocations,
4860 outputVariableIndex)))
4861 {
4862 // EXT_blend_func_extended: Linking can fail:
4863 // "if the explicit binding assignments do not leave enough space for the linker to
4864 // automatically assign a location for a varying out array, which requires multiple
4865 // contiguous locations."
4866 infoLog << "Could not fit output variable into available locations: "
4867 << outputVariable.name;
4868 return false;
4869 }
4870 }
4871
4872 return true;
4873}

4875void Program::setUniformValuesFromBindingQualifiers()
4876{
4877 for (unsigned int samplerIndex : mState.mExecutable->getSamplerUniformRange())
4878 {
4879 const auto &samplerUniform = mState.mExecutable->getUniforms()[samplerIndex];
4880 if (samplerUniform.binding != -1)
4881 {
4882 UniformLocation location = getUniformLocation(samplerUniform.name);
4883 ASSERT(location.value != -1);
4884 std::vector<GLint> boundTextureUnits;
4885 for (unsigned int elementIndex = 0;
4886 elementIndex < samplerUniform.getBasicTypeElementCount(); ++elementIndex)
4887 {
4888 boundTextureUnits.push_back(samplerUniform.binding + elementIndex);
4889 }
4890
4891 // Here we pass nullptr to avoid a large chain of calls that need a non-const Context.
4892 // We know it's safe not to notify the Context because this is only called after link.
4893 setUniform1iv(nullptr, location, static_cast<GLsizei>(boundTextureUnits.size()),
4894 boundTextureUnits.data());
4895 }
4896 }

4910void Program::updateSamplerUniform(Context *context,
4911 const VariableLocation &locationInfo,
4912 GLsizei clampedCount,
4913 const GLint *v)
4914{
4915 ASSERT(mState.isSamplerUniformIndex(locationInfo.index));
4916 GLuint samplerIndex = mState.getSamplerIndexFromUniformIndex(locationInfo.index);
4917 SamplerBinding &samplerBinding = mState.mExecutable->mSamplerBindings[samplerIndex];
4918 std::vector<GLuint> &boundTextureUnits = samplerBinding.boundTextureUnits;
4919
4920 if (locationInfo.arrayIndex >= boundTextureUnits.size())
4921 {
4922 return;
4923 }
4924 GLsizei safeUniformCount = std::min(
4925 clampedCount, static_cast<GLsizei>(boundTextureUnits.size() - locationInfo.arrayIndex));
4926
4927 // Update the sampler uniforms.
4928 for (GLsizei arrayIndex = 0; arrayIndex < safeUniformCount; ++arrayIndex)
4929 {
4930 GLint oldTextureUnit = boundTextureUnits[arrayIndex + locationInfo.arrayIndex];
4931 GLint newTextureUnit = v[arrayIndex];
4932
4933 if (oldTextureUnit == newTextureUnit)
4934 {
4935 continue;
4936 }
4937
4938 boundTextureUnits[arrayIndex + locationInfo.arrayIndex] = newTextureUnit;
4939
4940 // Update the reference counts.
4941 uint32_t &oldRefCount = mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplerRefCounts[oldTextureUnit];
4942 uint32_t &newRefCount = mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplerRefCounts[newTextureUnit];
4943 ASSERT(oldRefCount > 0);
4944 ASSERT(newRefCount < std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max());
4945 oldRefCount--;
4946 newRefCount++;
4947
4948 // Check for binding type change.
4949 TextureType &newSamplerType = mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplerTypes[newTextureUnit];
4950 TextureType &oldSamplerType = mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplerTypes[oldTextureUnit];
4951 SamplerFormat &newSamplerFormat = mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplerFormats[newTextureUnit];
4952 SamplerFormat &oldSamplerFormat = mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplerFormats[oldTextureUnit];
4953
4954 if (newRefCount == 1)
4955 {
4956 newSamplerType = samplerBinding.textureType;
4957 newSamplerFormat = samplerBinding.format;
4958 mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplersMask.set(newTextureUnit);
4959 mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplerShaderBits[newTextureUnit] =
4960 mState.mExecutable->getUniforms()[locationInfo.index].activeShaders();
4961 }
4962 else
4963 {
4964 if (newSamplerType != samplerBinding.textureType)
4965 {
4966 // Conflict detected. Ensure we reset it properly.
4967 newSamplerType = TextureType::InvalidEnum;
4968 }
4969 if (newSamplerFormat != samplerBinding.format)
4970 {
4971 newSamplerFormat = SamplerFormat::InvalidEnum;
4972 }
4973 }
4974
4975 // Unset previously active sampler.
4976 if (oldRefCount == 0)
4977 {
4978 oldSamplerType = TextureType::InvalidEnum;
4979 oldSamplerFormat = SamplerFormat::InvalidEnum;
4980 mState.mExecutable->mActiveSamplersMask.reset(oldTextureUnit);
4981 }
4982 else
4983 {
4984 if (oldSamplerType == TextureType::InvalidEnum ||
4985 oldSamplerFormat == SamplerFormat::InvalidEnum)
4986 {
4987 // Previous conflict. Check if this new change fixed the conflict.
4988 mState.setSamplerUniformTextureTypeAndFormat(oldTextureUnit);
4989 }
4990 }
4991
4992 // Notify context.
4993 if (context)
4994 {
4995 context->onSamplerUniformChange(newTextureUnit);
4996 context->onSamplerUniformChange(oldTextureUnit);
4997 }
4998 }
4999
5000 // Invalidate the validation cache.
5001 mCachedValidateSamplersResult.reset();
5002}

5010template <typename T>
5011GLsizei Program::clampUniformCount(const VariableLocation &locationInfo,
5012 GLsizei count,
5013 int vectorSize,
5014 const T *v)
5015{
5016 if (count == 1)
5017 return 1;
5018
5019 const LinkedUniform &linkedUniform = mState.mExecutable->getUniforms()[locationInfo.index];
5020
5021 // OpenGL ES 3.0.4 spec pg 67: "Values for any array element that exceeds the highest array
5022 // element index used, as reported by GetActiveUniform, will be ignored by the GL."
5023 unsigned int remainingElements =
5024 linkedUniform.getBasicTypeElementCount() - locationInfo.arrayIndex;
5025 GLsizei maxElementCount =
5026 static_cast<GLsizei>(remainingElements * linkedUniform.getElementComponents());
5027
5028 if (count * vectorSize > maxElementCount)
5029 {
5030 return maxElementCount / vectorSize;
5031 }
5032
5033 return count;
5034}
5035
5036template <size_t cols, size_t rows, typename T>
5037GLsizei Program::clampMatrixUniformCount(UniformLocation location,
5038 GLsizei count,
5039 GLboolean transpose,
5040 const T *v)
5041{
5042 const VariableLocation &locationInfo = mState.mUniformLocations[location.value];
5043
5044 if (!transpose)
5045 {
5046 return clampUniformCount(locationInfo, count, cols * rows, v);
5047 }
5048
5049 const LinkedUniform &linkedUniform = mState.mExecutable->getUniforms()[locationInfo.index];
5050
5051 // OpenGL ES 3.0.4 spec pg 67: "Values for any array element that exceeds the highest array
5052 // element index used, as reported by GetActiveUniform, will be ignored by the GL."
5053 unsigned int remainingElements =
5054 linkedUniform.getBasicTypeElementCount() - locationInfo.arrayIndex;
5055 return std::min(count, static_cast<GLsizei>(remainingElements));
5056}

5058// Driver differences mean that doing the uniform value cast ourselves gives consistent results.
5059// EG: on NVIDIA drivers, it was observed that getUniformi for MAX_INT+1 returned MIN_INT.
5060template <typename DestT>
5061void Program::getUniformInternal(const Context *context,
5062 DestT *dataOut,
5063 UniformLocation location,
5064 GLenum nativeType,
5065 int components) const
5066{
5067 switch (nativeType)
5068 {
5069 case GL_BOOL:
5070 {
5071 GLint tempValue[16] = {0};
5072 mProgram->getUniformiv(context, location.value, tempValue);
5073 UniformStateQueryCastLoop<GLboolean>(
5074 dataOut, reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(tempValue), components);
5075 break;
5076 }
5077 case GL_INT:
5078 {
5079 GLint tempValue[16] = {0};
5080 mProgram->getUniformiv(context, location.value, tempValue);
5081 UniformStateQueryCastLoop<GLint>(dataOut, reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(tempValue),
5082 components);
5083 break;
5084 }
5085 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
5086 {
5087 GLuint tempValue[16] = {0};
5088 mProgram->getUniformuiv(context, location.value, tempValue);
5089 UniformStateQueryCastLoop<GLuint>(dataOut, reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(tempValue),
5090 components);
5091 break;
5092 }
5093 case GL_FLOAT:
5094 {
5095 GLfloat tempValue[16] = {0};
5096 mProgram->getUniformfv(context, location.value, tempValue);
5097 UniformStateQueryCastLoop<GLfloat>(
5098 dataOut, reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(tempValue), components);
5099 break;
5100 }
5101 default:
5102 UNREACHABLE();
5103 break;
5104 }
5105}

5118
5119angle::Result Program::serialize(const Context *context, angle::MemoryBuffer *binaryOut) const
5120{
5121 BinaryOutputStream stream;
5122
5123 stream.writeBytes(reinterpret_cast<const unsigned char *>(ANGLE_COMMIT_HASH),
5124 ANGLE_COMMIT_HASH_SIZE);
5125
5126 // nullptr context is supported when computing binary length.
5127 if (context)
5128 {
5129 stream.writeInt(context->getClientVersion().major);
5130 stream.writeInt(context->getClientVersion().minor);
5131 }
5132 else
5133 {
5134 stream.writeInt(2);
5135 stream.writeInt(0);
5136 }
5137
5138 mState.mExecutable->save(&stream);
5139
5140 const auto &computeLocalSize = mState.getComputeShaderLocalSize();
5141
5142 stream.writeInt(computeLocalSize[0]);
5143 stream.writeInt(computeLocalSize[1]);
5144 stream.writeInt(computeLocalSize[2]);
5145
5146 ASSERT(mState.mGeometryShaderInvocations >= 1 && mState.mGeometryShaderMaxVertices >= 0);
5147 stream.writeEnum(mState.mGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType);
5148 stream.writeEnum(mState.mGeometryShaderOutputPrimitiveType);
5149 stream.writeInt(mState.mGeometryShaderInvocations);
5150 stream.writeInt(mState.mGeometryShaderMaxVertices);
5151
5152 stream.writeInt(mState.mNumViews);
5153 stream.writeBool(mState.mEarlyFramentTestsOptimization);
5154
5155 stream.writeInt(mState.getProgramInputs().size());
5156 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &attrib : mState.getProgramInputs())
5157 {
5158 WriteShaderVar(&stream, attrib);
5159 stream.writeInt(attrib.location);
5160 }
5161
5162 stream.writeInt(mState.getUniforms().size());
5163 for (const LinkedUniform &uniform : mState.getUniforms())
5164 {
5165 WriteShaderVar(&stream, uniform);
5166
5167 // FIXME: referenced
5168
5169 stream.writeInt(uniform.bufferIndex);
5170 WriteBlockMemberInfo(&stream, uniform.blockInfo);
5171
5172 stream.writeIntVector(uniform.outerArraySizes);
5173
5174 // Active shader info
5175 for (ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
5176 {
5177 stream.writeBool(uniform.isActive(shaderType));
5178 }
5179 }
5180
5181 stream.writeInt(mState.getUniformLocations().size());
5182 for (const auto &variable : mState.getUniformLocations())
5183 {
5184 stream.writeInt(variable.arrayIndex);
5185 stream.writeIntOrNegOne(variable.index);
5186 stream.writeBool(variable.ignored);
5187 }
5188
5189 stream.writeInt(mState.getUniformBlocks().size());
5190 for (const InterfaceBlock &uniformBlock : mState.getUniformBlocks())
5191 {
5192 WriteInterfaceBlock(&stream, uniformBlock);
5193 }
5194
5195 stream.writeInt(mState.getBufferVariables().size());
5196 for (const BufferVariable &bufferVariable : mState.getBufferVariables())
5197 {
5198 WriteBufferVariable(&stream, bufferVariable);
5199 }
5200
5201 stream.writeInt(mState.getShaderStorageBlocks().size());
5202 for (const InterfaceBlock &shaderStorageBlock : mState.getShaderStorageBlocks())
5203 {
5204 WriteInterfaceBlock(&stream, shaderStorageBlock);
5205 }
5206
5207 stream.writeInt(mState.mExecutable->mAtomicCounterBuffers.size());
5208 for (const AtomicCounterBuffer &atomicCounterBuffer :
5209 mState.mExecutable->getAtomicCounterBuffers())
5210 {
5211 WriteShaderVariableBuffer(&stream, atomicCounterBuffer);
5212 }
5213
5214 // Warn the app layer if saving a binary with unsupported transform feedback.
5215 if (!mState.getLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings().empty() &&
5216 context->getFrontendFeatures().disableProgramCachingForTransformFeedback.enabled)
5217 {
5218 WARN() << "Saving program binary with transform feedback, which is not supported on this "
5219 "driver.";
5220 }
5221
5222 stream.writeInt(mState.getLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings().size());
5223 for (const auto &var : mState.getLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings())
5224 {
5225 stream.writeIntVector(var.arraySizes);
5226 stream.writeInt(var.type);
5227 stream.writeString(var.name);
5228
5229 stream.writeIntOrNegOne(var.arrayIndex);
5230 }
5231
5232 stream.writeInt(mState.getTransformFeedbackBufferMode());
5233
5234 stream.writeInt(mState.getOutputVariables().size());
5235 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &output : mState.getOutputVariables())
5236 {
5237 WriteShaderVar(&stream, output);
5238 stream.writeInt(output.location);
5239 stream.writeInt(output.index);
5240 }
5241
5242 stream.writeInt(mState.getOutputLocations().size());
5243 for (const auto &outputVar : mState.getOutputLocations())
5244 {
5245 stream.writeInt(outputVar.arrayIndex);
5246 stream.writeIntOrNegOne(outputVar.index);
5247 stream.writeBool(outputVar.ignored);
5248 }
5249
5250 stream.writeInt(mState.getSecondaryOutputLocations().size());
5251 for (const auto &outputVar : mState.getSecondaryOutputLocations())
5252 {
5253 stream.writeInt(outputVar.arrayIndex);
5254 stream.writeIntOrNegOne(outputVar.index);
5255 stream.writeBool(outputVar.ignored);
5256 }
5257
5258 stream.writeInt(mState.mOutputVariableTypes.size());
5259 for (const auto &outputVariableType : mState.mOutputVariableTypes)
5260 {
5261 stream.writeInt(outputVariableType);
5262 }
5263
5264 static_assert(
5265 IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS * 2 <= 8 * sizeof(uint32_t),
5266 "All bits of mDrawBufferTypeMask and mActiveOutputVariables can be contained in 32 bits");
5267 stream.writeInt(static_cast<int>(mState.mDrawBufferTypeMask.to_ulong()));
5268 stream.writeInt(static_cast<int>(mState.mActiveOutputVariables.to_ulong()));
5269
5270 stream.writeInt(mState.getDefaultUniformRange().low());
5271 stream.writeInt(mState.getDefaultUniformRange().high());
5272
5273 stream.writeInt(mState.getSamplerUniformRange().low());
5274 stream.writeInt(mState.getSamplerUniformRange().high());
5275
5276 stream.writeInt(mState.getSamplerBindings().size());
5277 for (const auto &samplerBinding : mState.getSamplerBindings())
5278 {
5279 stream.writeEnum(samplerBinding.textureType);
5280 stream.writeEnum(samplerBinding.format);
5281 stream.writeInt(samplerBinding.boundTextureUnits.size());
5282 }
5283
5284 stream.writeInt(mState.getImageUniformRange().low());
5285 stream.writeInt(mState.getImageUniformRange().high());
5286
5287 stream.writeInt(mState.getImageBindings().size());
5288 for (const auto &imageBinding : mState.getImageBindings())
5289 {
5290 stream.writeInt(imageBinding.boundImageUnits.size());
5291 for (size_t i = 0; i < imageBinding.boundImageUnits.size(); ++i)
5292 {
5293 stream.writeInt(imageBinding.boundImageUnits[i]);
5294 }
5295 }
5296
5297 stream.writeInt(mState.getAtomicCounterUniformRange().low());
5298 stream.writeInt(mState.getAtomicCounterUniformRange().high());
5299
5300 mProgram->save(context, &stream);
5301
5302 ASSERT(binaryOut);
5303 if (!binaryOut->resize(stream.length()))
5304 {
5305 WARN() << "Failed to allocate enough memory to serialize a program. (" << stream.length()
5306 << " bytes )";
5307 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
5308 }
5309 memcpy(binaryOut->data(), stream.data(), stream.length());
5310 return angle::Result::Continue;
5311}
5312
5313angle::Result Program::deserialize(const Context *context,
5314 BinaryInputStream &stream,
5315 InfoLog &infoLog)
5316{
5317 unsigned char commitString[ANGLE_COMMIT_HASH_SIZE];
5318 stream.readBytes(commitString, ANGLE_COMMIT_HASH_SIZE);
5319 if (memcmp(commitString, ANGLE_COMMIT_HASH, sizeof(unsigned char) * ANGLE_COMMIT_HASH_SIZE) !=
5320 0)
5321 {
5322 infoLog << "Invalid program binary version.";
5323 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
5324 }
5325
5326 int majorVersion = stream.readInt<int>();
5327 int minorVersion = stream.readInt<int>();
5328 if (majorVersion != context->getClientMajorVersion() ||
5329 minorVersion != context->getClientMinorVersion())
5330 {
5331 infoLog << "Cannot load program binaries across different ES context versions.";
5332 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
5333 }
5334
5335 mState.mExecutable->load(&stream);
5336
5337 mState.mComputeShaderLocalSize[0] = stream.readInt<int>();
5338 mState.mComputeShaderLocalSize[1] = stream.readInt<int>();
5339 mState.mComputeShaderLocalSize[2] = stream.readInt<int>();
5340
5341 mState.mGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType = stream.readEnum<PrimitiveMode>();
5342 mState.mGeometryShaderOutputPrimitiveType = stream.readEnum<PrimitiveMode>();
5343 mState.mGeometryShaderInvocations = stream.readInt<int>();
5344 mState.mGeometryShaderMaxVertices = stream.readInt<int>();
5345
5346 mState.mNumViews = stream.readInt<int>();
5347 mState.mEarlyFramentTestsOptimization = stream.readBool();
5348
5349 size_t attribCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5350 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->getProgramInputs().empty());
5351 for (size_t attribIndex = 0; attribIndex < attribCount; ++attribIndex)
5352 {
5353 sh::ShaderVariable attrib;
5354 LoadShaderVar(&stream, &attrib);
5355 attrib.location = stream.readInt<int>();
5356 mState.mExecutable->mProgramInputs.push_back(attrib);
5357 }
5358
5359 size_t uniformCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5360 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->getUniforms().empty());
5361 for (size_t uniformIndex = 0; uniformIndex < uniformCount; ++uniformIndex)
5362 {
5363 LinkedUniform uniform;
5364 LoadShaderVar(&stream, &uniform);
5365
5366 uniform.bufferIndex = stream.readInt<int>();
5367 LoadBlockMemberInfo(&stream, &uniform.blockInfo);
5368
5369 stream.readIntVector<unsigned int>(&uniform.outerArraySizes);
5370
5371 uniform.typeInfo = &GetUniformTypeInfo(uniform.type);
5372
5373 // Active shader info
5374 for (ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
5375 {
5376 uniform.setActive(shaderType, stream.readBool());
5377 }
5378
5379 mState.mExecutable->mUniforms.push_back(uniform);
5380 }
5381
5382 const size_t uniformIndexCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5383 ASSERT(mState.mUniformLocations.empty());
5384 for (size_t uniformIndexIndex = 0; uniformIndexIndex < uniformIndexCount; ++uniformIndexIndex)
5385 {
5386 VariableLocation variable;
5387 stream.readInt(&variable.arrayIndex);
5388 stream.readInt(&variable.index);
5389 stream.readBool(&variable.ignored);
5390
5391 mState.mUniformLocations.push_back(variable);
5392 }
5393
5394 size_t uniformBlockCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5395 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->getUniformBlocks().empty());
5396 for (size_t uniformBlockIndex = 0; uniformBlockIndex < uniformBlockCount; ++uniformBlockIndex)
5397 {
5398 InterfaceBlock uniformBlock;
5399 LoadInterfaceBlock(&stream, &uniformBlock);
5400 mState.mExecutable->mUniformBlocks.push_back(uniformBlock);
5401
5402 mState.mActiveUniformBlockBindings.set(uniformBlockIndex, uniformBlock.binding != 0);
5403 }
5404
5405 size_t bufferVariableCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5406 ASSERT(mState.mBufferVariables.empty());
5407 for (size_t bufferVarIndex = 0; bufferVarIndex < bufferVariableCount; ++bufferVarIndex)
5408 {
5409 BufferVariable bufferVariable;
5410 LoadBufferVariable(&stream, &bufferVariable);
5411 mState.mBufferVariables.push_back(bufferVariable);
5412 }
5413
5414 size_t shaderStorageBlockCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5415 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->getShaderStorageBlocks().empty());
5416 for (size_t shaderStorageBlockIndex = 0; shaderStorageBlockIndex < shaderStorageBlockCount;
5417 ++shaderStorageBlockIndex)
5418 {
5419 InterfaceBlock shaderStorageBlock;
5420 LoadInterfaceBlock(&stream, &shaderStorageBlock);
5421 if (getExecutable().isCompute())
5422 {
5423 mState.mExecutable->mComputeShaderStorageBlocks.push_back(shaderStorageBlock);
5424 }
5425 else
5426 {
5427 mState.mExecutable->mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks.push_back(shaderStorageBlock);
5428 }
5429 }
5430
5431 size_t atomicCounterBufferCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5432 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->getAtomicCounterBuffers().empty());
5433 for (size_t bufferIndex = 0; bufferIndex < atomicCounterBufferCount; ++bufferIndex)
5434 {
5435 AtomicCounterBuffer atomicCounterBuffer;
5436 LoadShaderVariableBuffer(&stream, &atomicCounterBuffer);
5437
5438 mState.mExecutable->mAtomicCounterBuffers.push_back(atomicCounterBuffer);
5439 }
5440
5441 size_t transformFeedbackVaryingCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5442
5443 // Reject programs that use transform feedback varyings if the hardware cannot support them.
5444 if (transformFeedbackVaryingCount > 0 &&
5445 context->getFrontendFeatures().disableProgramCachingForTransformFeedback.enabled)
5446 {
5447 infoLog << "Current driver does not support transform feedback in binary programs.";
5448 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
5449 }
5450
5451 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings.empty());
5452 for (size_t transformFeedbackVaryingIndex = 0;
5453 transformFeedbackVaryingIndex < transformFeedbackVaryingCount;
5454 ++transformFeedbackVaryingIndex)
5455 {
5456 sh::ShaderVariable varying;
5457 stream.readIntVector<unsigned int>(&varying.arraySizes);
5458 stream.readInt(&varying.type);
5459 stream.readString(&varying.name);
5460
5461 GLuint arrayIndex = stream.readInt<GLuint>();
5462
5463 mState.mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings.emplace_back(varying, arrayIndex);
5464 }
5465
5466 stream.readInt(&mState.mExecutable->mTransformFeedbackBufferMode);
5467
5468 size_t outputCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5469 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->getOutputVariables().empty());
5470 for (size_t outputIndex = 0; outputIndex < outputCount; ++outputIndex)
5471 {
5472 sh::ShaderVariable output;
5473 LoadShaderVar(&stream, &output);
5474 output.location = stream.readInt<int>();
5475 output.index = stream.readInt<int>();
5476 mState.mExecutable->mOutputVariables.push_back(output);
5477 }
5478
5479 size_t outputVarCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5480 ASSERT(mState.mExecutable->getOutputLocations().empty());
5481 for (size_t outputIndex = 0; outputIndex < outputVarCount; ++outputIndex)
5482 {
5483 VariableLocation locationData;
5484 stream.readInt(&locationData.arrayIndex);
5485 stream.readInt(&locationData.index);
5486 stream.readBool(&locationData.ignored);
5487 mState.mExecutable->mOutputLocations.push_back(locationData);
5488 }
5489
5490 size_t secondaryOutputVarCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5491 ASSERT(mState.mSecondaryOutputLocations.empty());
5492 for (size_t outputIndex = 0; outputIndex < secondaryOutputVarCount; ++outputIndex)
5493 {
5494 VariableLocation locationData;
5495 stream.readInt(&locationData.arrayIndex);
5496 stream.readInt(&locationData.index);
5497 stream.readBool(&locationData.ignored);
5498 mState.mSecondaryOutputLocations.push_back(locationData);
5499 }
5500
5501 size_t outputTypeCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5502 for (size_t outputIndex = 0; outputIndex < outputTypeCount; ++outputIndex)
5503 {
5504 mState.mOutputVariableTypes.push_back(stream.readInt<GLenum>());
5505 }
5506
5507 static_assert(IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS * 2 <= 8 * sizeof(uint32_t),
5508 "All bits of mDrawBufferTypeMask and mActiveOutputVariables types and mask fit "
5509 "into 32 bits each");
5510 mState.mDrawBufferTypeMask = gl::ComponentTypeMask(stream.readInt<uint32_t>());
5511 mState.mActiveOutputVariables =
5512 gl::DrawBufferMask(stream.readInt<gl::DrawBufferMask::value_type>());
5513
5514 unsigned int defaultUniformRangeLow = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5515 unsigned int defaultUniformRangeHigh = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5516 mState.mExecutable->mDefaultUniformRange =
5517 RangeUI(defaultUniformRangeLow, defaultUniformRangeHigh);
5518
5519 unsigned int samplerRangeLow = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5520 unsigned int samplerRangeHigh = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5521 mState.mExecutable->mSamplerUniformRange = RangeUI(samplerRangeLow, samplerRangeHigh);
5522 size_t samplerCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5523 for (size_t samplerIndex = 0; samplerIndex < samplerCount; ++samplerIndex)
5524 {
5525 TextureType textureType = stream.readEnum<TextureType>();
5526 SamplerFormat format = stream.readEnum<SamplerFormat>();
5527 size_t bindingCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5528 mState.mExecutable->mSamplerBindings.emplace_back(textureType, format, bindingCount);
5529 }
5530
5531 unsigned int imageRangeLow = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5532 unsigned int imageRangeHigh = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5533 mState.mExecutable->mImageUniformRange = RangeUI(imageRangeLow, imageRangeHigh);
5534 size_t imageBindingCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5535 for (size_t imageIndex = 0; imageIndex < imageBindingCount; ++imageIndex)
5536 {
5537 size_t elementCount = stream.readInt<size_t>();
5538 ImageBinding imageBinding(elementCount);
5539 for (size_t elementIndex = 0; elementIndex < elementCount; ++elementIndex)
5540 {
5541 imageBinding.boundImageUnits[elementIndex] = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5542 }
5543 if (getExecutable().isCompute())
5544 {
5545 mState.mExecutable->mComputeImageBindings.emplace_back(imageBinding);
5546 }
5547 else
5548 {
5549 mState.mExecutable->mGraphicsImageBindings.emplace_back(imageBinding);
5550 }
5551 }
5552
5553 unsigned int atomicCounterRangeLow = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5554 unsigned int atomicCounterRangeHigh = stream.readInt<unsigned int>();
5555 mState.mAtomicCounterUniformRange = RangeUI(atomicCounterRangeLow, atomicCounterRangeHigh);
5556
5557 static_assert(static_cast<unsigned long>(ShaderType::EnumCount) <= sizeof(unsigned long) * 8,
5558 "Too many shader types");
5559
5560 if (!mState.mAttachedShaders[ShaderType::Compute])
5561 {
5562 mState.updateTransformFeedbackStrides();
5563 }
5564
5565 postResolveLink(context);
5566 mState.mExecutable->updateCanDrawWith();
5567
5568 return angle::Result::Continue;
5569}
5570
5571void Program::postResolveLink(const gl::Context *context)
5572{
5573 mState.updateActiveSamplers();
5574 mState.mExecutable->updateActiveImages(getExecutable());
5575
5576 setUniformValuesFromBindingQualifiers();
5577
5578 if (context->getExtensions().multiDraw)
5579 {
5580 mState.mDrawIDLocation = getUniformLocation("gl_DrawID").value;
5581 }
5582
5583 if (context->getExtensions().baseVertexBaseInstance)
5584 {
5585 mState.mBaseVertexLocation = getUniformLocation("gl_BaseVertex").value;
5586 mState.mBaseInstanceLocation = getUniformLocation("gl_BaseInstance").value;
5587 }
5588}

5590void Program::fillProgramStateMap(ShaderMap<const ProgramState *> *programStatesOut)
5591{
5592 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
5593 {
5594 (*programStatesOut)[shaderType] = nullptr;
5595 if (mState.getExecutable().hasLinkedShaderStage(shaderType) ||
5596 mState.getAttachedShader(shaderType))
5597 {
5598 (*programStatesOut)[shaderType] = &mState;
5599 }
5600 }
